{{nihongo|'''Takehiro Tomiyasu'''|冨安 健洋|Tomiyasu Takehiro|born 5 November 1998}} is a Japanese professional [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for {{Dutch football updater|Ajax}} club [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] and currently plays for the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]]. Mainly a [[full-back (association football)|full back]], he can also be deployed as a [[centre-back]].

Beginning his career at [[Avispa Fukuoka]], Tomiyasu had a spell with Belgian club [[Sint-Truidense V.V.|Sint-Truiden]] and Italian club [[Bologna FC 1909|Bologna]] before joining Arsenal in 2021 for a reported fee of up to £17m.

Having previously played for various youth levels, Tomiyasu received a call-up for Japan's senior team in 2018. He featured for the side that reached the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup final|final]] of the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]], and also played at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] and [[2023 AFC Asian Cup|2023 Asian Cup]].

==Club career==
===Avispa Fukuoka===
Born in [[Fukuoka]], Japan, Tomiyasu enrolled at Sanchiku Elementary School, and during the second half of his first grade, he joined the school’s football club, Sanchiku Kickers, where he initially played as a defensive midfielder. He was scouted by the club’s general manager, Kanji Tsuji, who was impressed by his performance, particularly his speed, and encouraged his parents to support his football development.<ref name="Tomiyasu Interview 1">{{cite news |date=31 January 2018 |title=サッカー日本代表の"新星"ＤＦ冨安健洋、成長の背景にあるものとは |url=https://www.sponichi.co.jp/soccer/news/2018/10/31/kiji/20181030s00002014373000c.html |access-date=19 April 2020 |publisher=Sponichi Annex |language=ja}}</ref><ref name="JR Soccer">{{cite news |date=16 November 2018 |title=「バルサに推薦」できるほどの潜在能力。次世代の日本代表DF・冨安健洋の少年時代 |url=https://jr-soccer.jp/2018/11/16/post64933/ |access-date=19 April 2020 |publisher=JR Soccer |language=ja}}</ref>

In 2009, when he was eleven years old and in the fifth grade, Tomiyasu began attending the newly established [[FC Barcelona]] Academy in Fukuoka, training there twice a week. At the academy, he played as a defensive midfielder. Although there were discussions about the possibility of joining FC Barcelona’s youth setup in Spain, the move did not materialize.<ref>{{cite news |date=30 April 2017 |title=18歳のJリーガー冨安健洋を支えるバルサスクールでの経験（前編） |url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/jl/20170430/582021.html |access-date=19 April 2020 |publisher=Soccer King |language=ja}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=16 November 2018 |title=「バルサに推薦」できるほどの潜在能力。次世代の日本代表DF・冨安健洋の少年時代 2 |url=https://jr-soccer.jp/2018/11/16/post64933/2/ |access-date=19 April 2020 |publisher=JR Soccer |language=ja}}<br />{{cite web |date=19 January 2019 |title=バルサアカデミー出身選手、コパ・アジア準決勝へ |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.jp/ja/club/news/982730/ |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240907092413/https://www.fcbarcelona.jp/ja/club/news/982730/ |archive-date=7 September 2024 |access-date=12 September 2024 |website=FC Barcelona |language=es}}</ref>

After graduating from elementary school at the age of 12, Tomiyasu passed the selection trial and joined the local club [[Avispa Fukuoka]]’s junior youth team.<ref name="Tomiyasu Interview 1" /> By the age of 14, he was playing for their U-15 side and was also selected for the Japan national youth team.<ref name="Tomiyasu Interview 1" /><ref>{{cite news |date=16 November 2018 |title=「バルサに推薦」できるほどの潜在能力。次世代の日本代表DF・冨安健洋の少年時代 |url=https://jr-soccer.jp/2018/11/16/post64933/3/ |access-date=19 April 2020 |publisher=JR Soccer |language=ja}}</ref> Initially playing in the midfield position, he switched to [[centre back]].<ref>{{cite news|title=18歳のJリーガー冨安健洋を支えるバルサスクールでの経験（後編）|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/world/esp/20170430/582031.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=ja|date=30 April 2017|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> During his time at Avispa Fukuoka's youth system, Tomiyasu had a period as the club captain.<ref name="Tomiyasu Interview 1" /><ref>{{cite news |date=4 May 2013 |title=[JFA プレミアカップ2013]2年生FW吉岡ハット!京都U-15が福岡U-15下し、3度目Vへあと1勝 |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?114204-118169-fl |access-date=19 April 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}<br />{{cite news |date=2 November 2013 |title=[2013Jユースカップ]アビスパ福岡U-18メンバーリスト |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?123209-127944-fl |access-date=19 April 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}<br />{{cite news |date=21 March 2015 |title=福岡U-18の長身ボランチ、冨安がCBとしてU-17日本代表の守りに安定もたらす |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?159234-159234-fl |access-date=19 April 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}</ref> He impressed at the 2013's JFA Premier Cup, and was named in the Best Eleven as a result.<ref>{{cite news |date=6 June 2013 |title=[JFA プレミアカップ2013]優勝した大宮ジュニアユースから2人、準V・京都U-15からは4人がベストイレブンに |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?114260-118245-fl |access-date=19 April 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}</ref> In May 2015, it was announced that Avispa Fukuoka had registered Tomiyasu.<ref>{{cite news |date=20 May 2015 |title=登録選手追加・変更・抹消のお知らせ |url=https://www.jleague.jp/release/post-35313/ |access-date=12 September 2024 |publisher=J. League Official Website |language=ja}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 14 October 2015 as a starter in a 2–0 loss against [[FC Machida Zelvia|Machida Zelvia]] in the third round of the Emperor's Cup.<ref>{{cite news|title=町田vs福岡 試合記録|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?174120-174120-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=14 October 2015|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2015 season, Tomiyasu signed a temporary contract with Avispa Fukuoka.<ref>{{cite news |date=8 December 2015 |title=福岡、U－18所属DF冨安健洋の加入内定を発表「J1の舞台で1日でも早くプレーしたい」 |url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/youthstudent/pro/20151208/421552.html |access-date=12 September 2024 |publisher=Soccer King |language=ja}}</ref>

At the start of the 2016 season, Tomiyasu spent the first half of the J League season on the substitute bench.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_160521|title=2016 明治安田生命J1リーグ <1stステージ> 第13節 vs. 柏レイソル|website=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=21 May 2016|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160524035518/http://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_160521|archive-date=24 May 2016|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|url=http://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_ync160525|title=2016ヤマザキナビスコカップ 第6節 vs. サガン鳥栖|website=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=29 May 2016|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160529033234/http://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_ync160525|archive-date=29 May 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> he made his first appearance of the season on 20 April 2016, as a starter in the defensive midfield position, in a 0–0 draw against [[Vegalta Sendai]] in the J League Cup.<ref>{{cite web |date=20 April 2016 |title=2016ヤマザキナビスコカップ 第4節 vs. ベガルタ仙台 |url=http://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_ync160420 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160423185330/http://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_ync160420 |archive-date=23 April 2016 |access-date=12 September 2024 |website=Avispa Fukuoka |language=ja}}</ref> However, in the J. League Cup match against [[Sagan Tosu]], Tomiyasu was sent off for a second bookable offence in a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_ync160525|title=2016ヤマザキナビスコカップ 第6節 vs. サガン鳥栖|website=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=25 May 2016|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160529033234/http://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_ync160525|archive-date=29 May 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Two months later, on 13 July 2016, he made his league debut for the club, starting in the defensive midfield position in a 2–1 win against [[FC Tokyo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_160713|title=2016 明治安田生命J1リーグ <2ndステージ> 第3節 vs. FC東京|publisher=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=13 July 2016|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200418165017/https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_160713|archive-date=18 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> After making his debut for the club, Tomiyasu became a regular for the side, usually playing in the defensive midfield position.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_160814|title=2016 明治安田生命J1リーグ <2ndステージ> 第8節 vs. 鹿島アントラーズ|website=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=14 August 2016|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817203041/http://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_160814|archive-date=17 August 2016|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|url=http://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_160831|title= 2016 JリーグYBCルヴァンカップ 準々決勝 第1戦 vs. ＦＣ東京|website=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=31 August 2016|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160901235854/http://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_160831|archive-date=1 September 2016|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_160917|title=2016 明治安田生命J1リーグ <2ndステージ> 第12節 vs. 湘南ベルマーレ|website=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=17 September 2016|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161004094136/http://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_160917|archive-date=4 October 2016|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|url=http://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_160925|title=2016 明治安田生命J1リーグ <2ndステージ> 第13節 vs. ヴィッセル神戸|website=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=25 September 2016|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161007031752/http://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_160925|archive-date=7 October 2016|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite news|title=福岡の規格外ジャイアント・冨安健洋が世界切符へのカギを握る|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?200295-200295-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=6 October 2016|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> It was reported on 26 September 2016 that he had become the second player in the league to be the fastest player at 12.436&nbsp;km in.<ref>{{cite news|title=最も走ったチーム&選手は…J1第2S第13節の走行距離発表|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?199539-199539-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=26 September 2016|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> Following the club's relegation to J. League 2, Tomiyasu went on to make sixteen appearances in all competitions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avispa.co.jp/news/post-7251|title=本日の試合結果を受けてのご報告|website=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=1 October 2016|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161005090700/http://www.avispa.co.jp/news/post-7251|archive-date=5 October 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> At the end of the 2016 season, he had his contract with the club renewed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/news/post-8389|title=冨安 健洋 選手 契約更新のお知らせ|publisher=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=28 December 2016|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200418164957/https://www.avispa.co.jp/news/post-8389|archive-date=18 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>

In the 2017 season, Tomiyasu became a regular for the side, playing at centre back.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_170226|title=2017 明治安田生命J2リーグ 第1節 vs.大分トリニータ|website=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=26 February 2017|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200929235027/https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_170226|archive-date=29 September 2020|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_170305|title=2017 明治安田生命J2リーグ 第2節 vs.レノファ山口ＦＣ|website=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=5 March 2017|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200930005558/https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_170305|archive-date=30 September 2020|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_170312|title=2017 明治安田生命J2リーグ 第3節 vs.京都サンガF.C.|website=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=12 March 2017|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20201124033349/https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_170312|archive-date=24 November 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He then scored his first goal for the club, in a 2–1 win against [[Roasso Kumamoto]] on 19 March 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_170319|title=2017 明治安田生命J2リーグ 第4節 vs.ロアッソ熊本|publisher=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=19 March 2017|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419084339/https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_170319|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> However, Tomiyasu faced two separate international commitment between March and May.<ref>{{cite news|title=3連勝中の福岡が"初づくし"の勝ち点1…山形は4戦連続ドロー|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?212285-212285-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=26 March 2017|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title=「自分はちゃんと成長できているのか…」 福岡DF冨安健洋、ストイックな18歳の葛藤|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?221290-221290-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=19 July 2017|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref><ref name="Tomiyasu Return">{{cite news |date=10 June 2017 |title=世界を知った18歳…伸びしろ十分の福岡DF冨安「プロの世界は簡単ではない」 |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?218562-218562-fl |access-date=19 April 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}</ref> Despite this, he continued to regain his first-team place for the club for the rest of the season.<ref name="Tomiyasu Return"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_170617|title=2017 明治安田生命J2リーグ 第19節 vs.名古屋グランパス|website=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=17 June 2017|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200924153720/https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_170617|archive-date=24 September 2020|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_170716|title=2017 明治安田生命J2リーグ 第23節 vs.ザスパクサツ群|publisher=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=16 July 2017|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419093015/https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_170716|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_171105|title=2017 明治安田生命J2リーグ 第40節 vs.湘南ベルマーレ|publisher=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=5 November 2018|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419093010/https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_171105|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Tomiyasu then helped Avispa Fukuoka three clean sheets in three matches between 29 July 2017 and 11 August 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_170729|title=2017 明治安田生命J2リーグ 第25節 vs.モンテディオ山形|publisher=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=29 July 2017|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419090109/https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_170729|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_170805|title=2017 明治安田生命J2リーグ 第26節 vs.ＦＣ町田ゼルビア|publisher=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=5 August 2017|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419090107/https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_170805|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_170811|title=2017 明治安田生命J2リーグ 第27節 vs.京都サンガF.C.|website=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=11 August 2016|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419090104/https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_170811|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He later helped the club qualify for the [[2017 J2 League#Playoffs|J1 League Promotion Playoffs]], having finished fourth place in the league.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_171105|title=2017 明治安田生命J2リーグ 第40節 vs.湘南ベルマーレ|website=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=5 November 2017|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419093010/https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_171105|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite news|title=炸裂する攻撃的サッカー。エスナイデル率いるジェフ千葉のミラクル昇格なるか。|url=https://news.yahoo.co.jp/byline/sugiyamashigeki/20171124-00078493/|publisher=Yahoo News|language=ja|date=24 November 2017|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title=ジェフ千葉、ミラクル昇格に望み。 アルゼンチン流攻撃サッカーが炸裂|url=https://sportiva.shueisha.co.jp/clm/football/jleague_other/2017/11/21/post_52/|publisher=Sportiva Shueisha|language=ja|date=21 November 2017|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> Tomiyasu helped the side beat [[Tokyo Verdy]] 1–0 to reach the semi–finals of the J1 League Promotion Playoffs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_171127|title=2017 J1昇格プレーオフ 準決勝 vs. 東京ヴェルディ|publisher=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=26 November 2017|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419093747/https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_171127|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> In the final of the J1 League Promotion Playoffs against [[Nagoya Grampus]], Tomiyasu played 90 minutes, as they drew 0–0 but saw Avispa Fukuoka unsuccessfully promoted to J. League One.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_171203|title=2017 J1昇格プレーオフ 決勝 vs. 名古屋グランパス|website=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=3 December 2017|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200921153736/https://www.avispa.co.jp/game-result/game_file_171203|archive-date=21 September 2020|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite news|title=鬼気迫るプレー見せた福岡DF冨安健洋、J1昇格逃し「悔しいです」|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?232427-232427-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=3 December 2017|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2017 season, he went on to make thirty–nine appearances and scoring once in all competitions.

===Sint-Truidense===
It was announced on 8 January 2018 that Tomiyasu would be moving abroad for the first time in his career by joining [[Belgian First Division A]] side [[Sint-Truidense V.V.|Sint-Truiden]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/news/post-15353|title=冨安 健洋 選手 シント＝トロイデンVV（ベルギー１部リーグ）へ完全移籍のお知らせ|publisher=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=8 January 2018|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419095936/https://www.avispa.co.jp/news/post-15353|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He signed a three-and-a-half-year contract with the club, keeping him until 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stvv.com/nl/nieuws/a-kern/takehiro-tomiyasu-is-een-kanarie|title=TAKEHIRO TOMIYASU IS EEN KANARIE!|publisher=Sint-Truidense V.V.|language=nl|date=16 January 2018|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419101510/https://www.stvv.com/nl/nieuws/a-kern/takehiro-tomiyasu-is-een-kanarie|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Upon joining the club, Tomiyasu said: "I want to become a special player in Belgium."<ref>{{cite news|title="IK DROOM VAN DE PREMIER LEAGUE"|url=https://www.hbvl.be/cnt/dmf20180321_03422889/ik-droom-van-de-premier-league|publisher=HBVL|language=nl|date=21 March 2018|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> After spending months at training and recovering from an ankle injury, Tomiyasu made his Sint-Truiden debut for the club, coming on as a late substitute, in a 2–1 win against [[Royal Antwerp F.C.|Royal Antwerp]] on 12 May 2018.<ref>{{cite news|title=CLUBNIEUWS. Weer slecht nieuws voor Anderlecht: Kums kampt met slepende blessure|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20180221_03369118|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=21 February 2018|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite web|url=https://www.stvv.com/nl/nieuws/a-kern/wedstrijdverslag-antwerp-vs-stvv-v1|title=STVV WINT LAATSTE UITWEDSTRIJD BIJ ANTWERP!|publisher=Sint-Truidense V.V.|language=nl|date=12 May 2018|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419122609/https://www.stvv.com/nl/nieuws/a-kern/wedstrijdverslag-antwerp-vs-stvv-v1|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite news|title=Teixeira fit voor Charleroi, Tomiyasu mikt op play-offs|url=https://www.hbvl.be/cnt/dmf20180228_03383669/teixeira-fit-voor-charleroi-tomiyasu-mikt-op-play-offs|publisher=HBVL|language=nl|date=28 February 2018|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> This turned out to be his only appearance of the 2017–18 season.

In the 2018–19 season, Tomiyasu made his first start for Sint-Truiden and played the entirety of a 0–0 draw against [[Cercle Brugge KSV|Cercle Brugge]] in the opening game of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stvv.com/nl/nieuws/a-kern/stvv-en-cercle-delen-de-punten|title=STVV EN CERCLE DELEN DE PUNTEN|publisher=Sint-Truidense V.V.|language=nl|date=28 July 2018|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419123033/https://www.stvv.com/nl/nieuws/a-kern/stvv-en-cercle-delen-de-punten|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Since the start of the season, he became a regular for the side, playing at centre back.<ref>{{cite news |date=17 August 2018 |title="Ik wil mijn fout rechtzetten" |url=https://www.hbvl.be/cnt/dmf20180817_03671012/ik-wil-mijn-fout-rechtzetten |access-date=19 April 2020 |publisher=HBVL |language=nl}}<br />{{cite news |date=26 November 2018 |title=PAS 20 EN AL EEN FENOMEEN |url=https://www.hbvl.be/cnt/dmf20181126_03989345/pas-20-en-al-een-fenomeen |access-date=19 April 2020 |publisher=HBVL |language=nl}}<br />{{cite news |date=26 November 2018 |title=Kenners analyseren Takehiro Tomiyasu, het Japanse goudhaantje in de Truiense defensie |url=https://www.hbvl.be/cnt/dmf20181126_03988901/pas-20-en-al-een-fenomeen |access-date=19 April 2020 |publisher=HBVL |language=nl}}<br />{{cite news |date=28 December 2018 |title=冨安健洋の市場価値が急騰!異例の17倍増でジュピラーリーグ最高価格のDFに |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?262653-262653-fl |access-date=19 April 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}</ref> Between 23 September 2018 and 30 September 2018, Tomiyasu kept three consecutive clean sheets in three matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stvv.com/nl/nieuws/a-kern/wedstrijdverslag-stvv-vs-antwerp-v1|title=STVV KLOPT RAFC MET 2–0!|publisher=Sint-Truidense V.V.|language=nl|date=22 September 2018|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419123947/https://www.stvv.com/nl/nieuws/a-kern/wedstrijdverslag-stvv-vs-antwerp-v1|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|url=https://www.stvv.com/nl/nieuws/a-kern/croky-cup-stvv-kfc-duffel-3-0|title=CROKY CUP: STVV-KFC DUFFEL 3–0|publisher=Sint-Truidense V.V.|language=nl|date=26 September 2018|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419123945/https://www.stvv.com/nl/nieuws/a-kern/croky-cup-stvv-kfc-duffel-3-0|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|url=https://www.stvv.com/nl/nieuws/a-kern/wedstrijdverslag-anderlecht-vs-stvv-v1|title=STVV PAKT MET TIEN EEN PUNT BIJ ANDERLECHT|publisher=Sint-Truidense V.V.|language=nl|date=30 September 2018|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419123942/https://www.stvv.com/nl/nieuws/a-kern/wedstrijdverslag-anderlecht-vs-stvv-v1|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Tomiyasu scored his first goal of the season on 25 November 2018 in a 4–2 win against [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stvv.com/nl/nieuws/a-kern/stvv-wint-spectaculaire-topper-tegen-anderlecht-met-4-2|title=WINT SPECTACULAIRE TOPPER TEGEN ANDERLECHT MET 4–2!|publisher=Sint-Truidense V.V.|language=nl|date=25 November 2018|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419123949/https://www.stvv.com/nl/nieuws/a-kern/stvv-wint-spectaculaire-topper-tegen-anderlecht-met-4-2|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> After spending January on international duty with Japan, Tomiyasu returned to Sint-Truidense on 9 February 2019, starting and playing the full 90 minutes in a 2–1 win against [[Waasland-Beveren]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Strijd voor Anderlecht om Play-off 1 barst nu echt los: hoe ziet het programma eruit en wie heeft de beste kaarten?|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20190208_04161371|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=2 February 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite web|url=https://www.stvv.com/nl/nieuws/a-kern/kanaries-pakken-9-op-9-na-winst-tegen-waasland-beveren|title=KANARIES PAKKEN 9 OP 9 NA WINST TEGEN WAASLAND-BEVEREN!|publisher=Sint-Truidense V.V.|language=nl|date=9 February 2019|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419123940/https://www.stvv.com/nl/nieuws/a-kern/kanaries-pakken-9-op-9-na-winst-tegen-waasland-beveren|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He continued to retain his place in the team for the rest of the 2018–19 season.<ref>{{cite news|title=冨安健洋、今夏の移籍は既定路線か…指揮官は最低額に言及「それ以下で出すのはクレイジー」|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?267518-267518-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=2 March 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title=鎌田が得点ランク3位の14点目&関根PK獲得も…遠藤負傷&冨安が失点に絡んだシントトロイデン、連勝は2でストップ|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?270859-270859-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=7 April 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title=1年の成長振り返る冨安健洋「開幕から信じて使ってくれた監督に感謝したい」|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?274767-274767-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=19 May 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> His performance received praise from the Belgian media.<ref>{{cite news|title=前節初得点、冨安健洋の鉄人ぶりにベルギーメディアが注目「現象になりつつある」|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?260238-260238-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=28 November 2018|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title=冨安健洋がベルギーメディアによる前半戦ベストイレブンに選出「絶大なインパクトを残した」|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?262784-262784-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=29 December 2018|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> As a result, he won the club's Player of the Year.<ref>{{cite news |date=31 March 2019 |title=Tomiyasu gekroond tot Speler van het Jaar |url=https://www.hbvl.be/cnt/dmf20190331_04293108/tomiyasu-gekroond-tot-speler-van-het-jaar |access-date=19 April 2020 |publisher=HBVL |language=nl}}<br />{{cite news |date=1 April 2019 |title=冨安健洋、ファン選出のシーズンMVPに「ありがたいですし見合った活躍を」 |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?270250-270250-fl |access-date=19 April 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}</ref> In his second season at Sint-Truidense, Tomiyasu made 40 appearances and scored once in all competitions.

===Bologna===
[[File:Takehiro Tomiyasu.jpg|thumb|Tomiyasu in 2020 with [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]].]]

It was reported on 29 June 2019 that [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]] agreed a €9&nbsp;million deal to sign Tomiyasu.<ref>{{cite news|title=CLUBNIEUWS. Mirallas wil terugkeren naar België, Standard haalt spelverdeler en Lamkel Zé stuurt zijn kat|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20190619_04469832|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=19 June 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title=STVV verkoopt Japanner Tomiyasu voor recordbedrag aan Bologna|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20190629_04486126|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=29 June 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> The transfer move was confirmed on 9 July 2019 and Tomiyasu became the second Japanese player to join the club after [[Hidetoshi Nakata]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Officieel: Takehiro Tomiyasu ruilt STVV voor recordbedrag|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20190709_04501753|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=9 July 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br / >{{cite web|url=https://www.bolognafc.it/takehiro-tomiyasu-al-bologna/|title=Takehiro Tomiyasu al Bologna|publisher=Bologna F.C. 1909|language=it|date=9 July 2019|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419135700/https://www.bolognafc.it/takehiro-tomiyasu-al-bologna/|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}< br />{{cite news|title=Bologna Fc mercato, ufficiale Takehiro Tomiyasu|url=https://www.ilrestodelcarlino.it/bologna/fc/mercato-tomiyasu-1.4686032|publisher=Il Resto del Carlino|language=it|date=9 July 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> Upon joining the club, he said: "Impression that the defensive tactics are detailed. The striker level is also very high. I chose this team because I wanted to learn individual defense tactics. First I wanted to be on the pitch."<ref>{{cite news |date=23 July 2019 |title=冨安健洋がボローニャ入団会見「個人戦術学びたい」 |url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/world/news/201907230001168.html |access-date=19 April 2020 |publisher=Nikkan Sports |language=it}}</ref>

Tomiyasu made his Bologna debut, playing the whole game, in a 3–0 win against [[A.C. Pisa 1909|Pisa]] in the first round of the [[Coppa Italia]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Coppa Italia, Bologna travolgente a Pisa (3–0) telecomandato da Sinisa|url=https://bologna.repubblica.it/sport/2019/08/18/news/coppa_italia_pisa-bologna-233880904/|publisher=La Repubblica|language=it|date=18 August 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> A week later, he made his league debut, playing the full 90 minutes of a 1–1 draw against [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Verona-Bologna 1–1, Miguel Veloso risponde a Sansone. Ma la vera vittoria è di Mihajlovic|url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/serie-a/bologna/2019/08/25/news/verona_bologna_mihajlovic-234347975/|publisher=La Repubblica|language=it|date=25 August 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> and was named Man of the Match for his performance.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bolognafc.it/tomiyasu-mvp-di-veronabfc/|title=Tomiyasu MVP di #VeronaBFC|publisher=Bologna F.C. 1909|language=it|date=27 August 2019|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419135641/https://www.bolognafc.it/tomiyasu-mvp-di-veronabfc/|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Having made three appearances, he was named August's Player of the Month.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bolognafc.it/tomiyasu-mvp-del-mese-di-agosto/|title=Tomiyasu MVP del mese di Agosto|publisher=Bologna F.C. 1909|language=it|date=12 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419135646/https://www.bolognafc.it/tomiyasu-mvp-del-mese-di-agosto/|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He started in the first league seven matches before suffering a hamstring injury in October that kept him out for a month.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bologna Fc, Tomiyasu infortunato. Stop di un mese|url=https://www.ilrestodelcarlino.it/bologna/fc/tomiyasu-infortunato-1.4837512|publisher=il Resto Del Carlino|language=it|date=16 October 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title=Incredibile Bologna: rimonta da 1–3 e vince 4–3 contro il Brescia in dieci|url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Bologna/15-09-2019/incredibile-bologna-brescia-va-sotto-3-1-poi-vince-orsolini-3402513838154.shtml|publisher=Le Gazzetta Dello Sport|language=it|date=15 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title=Genoa-Bologna 0–0: traversa di Schoene, Sansone sbaglia un rigore|url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/serie-a/2019/09/25/news/genoa_bologna_partita-236946446/|publisher=La Repubblica|language=it|date=25 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> On 24 November, he made his return to the starting line-up in a 2–2 draw against [[Parma Calcio 1913|Parma]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Fatto il trapianto come corre Sinisa Il Bologna ci prova|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2019/11/23/fatto-il-trapianto-come-corre-sinisa-il-bologna-ci-provaBologna15.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=23 November 2019|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Bologna Parma 2–2, Dzemaili "Non siamo contenti, volevamo vincere"|url=https://www.ilrestodelcarlino.it/bologna/fc/parma-dzemaili-1.4903737|publisher=Il Resto del Carlino|language=it|date=24 November 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> Since joining the club, Tomiyasu quickly established himself in the starting line-up playing at [[right back]], and his performances impressed the Italian media and supporters alike.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bologna, Tomiyasu nuova superstar rossoblù|url=https://corrieredibologna.corriere.it/bologna/bologna-calcio/19_settembre_09/tomiyasusuperstar-f990737c-d2d1-11e9-a0f3-f38e83028bdf.shtml|publisher=Corriere Di Bologna|language=it|date=9 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title=Mancherà anche il goleador eppure si marcia a due reti alla volta|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2019/12/16/manchera-anche-il-goleador-eppure-si-marcia-a-due-reti-alla-voltaBologna02.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=16 December 2019|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Straricco e di sinistra il Bologna si noterà?|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2020/01/02/straricco-e-di-sinistra-il-bologna-si-noteraBologna12.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=2 January 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Mezzi rigori e gol mangiati l'esito è giusto|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2020/01/26/mezzi-rigori-e-gol-mangiati-lesito-e-giustoBologna11.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=26 January 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Tomiyasu, il samurai di Sinisa: aspettando i Giochi, s'è preso il Bologna|url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Bologna/26-03-2020/aspettando-giochi-tomiyasu-s-preso-bologna-sinisa-3602004521014_preview.shtml?refresh_ce-cp|publisher=Le Gazzetta Dello Sport|language=it|date=26 March 2020|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> By the time the season was suspended because of the [[COVID-19 pandemic in Italy|COVID-19 pandemic]], he had made 20 appearances in all competitions.<ref>{{cite news|title=Emergenza Coronavirus: confermato lo stop alle attività fino al 3 aprile|url=https://www.figc.it/it/federazione/news/emergenza-coronavirus-confermato-lo-stop-alle-attivit%C3%A0-fino-al-3-aprile/|website=[[Italian Football Federation]]|language=it|date=20 March 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> Tomiyasu remained an integral part of the club once the season resumed behind closed doors.<ref>{{cite news|title=LA SERIE A TIM TORNA DAL 20 GIUGNO CON I RECUPERI DELLA SESTA GIORNATA DI RITORNO|url=https://www.legaseriea.it/it/sala-stampa/notizie/info/la-serie-a-tim-torna-dal-20-giugno-con-i-recuperi-della-sesta-giornata-di-ritorno|website=[[Italian Football Federation]]|language=it|date=19 May 2020|access-date=13 August 2021|archive-date=13 August 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210813215839/https://www.legaseriea.it/it/sala-stampa/notizie/info/la-serie-a-tim-torna-dal-20-giugno-con-i-recuperi-della-sesta-giornata-di-ritorno|url-status=dead}}<br />{{cite news|title=La parola alla difesa Dijks è già sotto esame|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2020/06/14/la-parola-alla-difesa-dijks-e-gia-sotto-esameBologna13.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=14 June 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=21歳冨安健洋がセリエA再開へ意気込み「ボローニャにとってより重要な選手に」|url=https://www.goal.com/jp/%E3%83%8B%E3%83%A5%E3%83%BC%E3%82%B9/takehiro-tomiyasu-bologna-20200619/1h5whrcyamot11989zbi75idiz|website=Goal (website)|language=it|date=21 June 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Questo calcio somiglia troppo alla playstation|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2020/07/16/questo-calcio-somiglia-troppo-alla-playstationBologna10.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=16 July 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Sinisa è già nel futuro "Qui serve un bomber"|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2020/07/18/sinisa-e-gia-nel-futuro-qui-serve-un-bomberBologna11.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=18 July 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Bologna in the 44th minute with his left foot, in a 5–1 loss against [[A.C. Milan|Milan]] on 18 July 2020.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bologna umiliato dal Milan: cinque schiaffi a San Siro|url=https://corrieredibologna.corriere.it/bologna/bologna-calcio/20_luglio_18/bologna-umiliato-milan-cinque-schiaffi-san-siro-b9e3921a-c941-11ea-9c99-73c035e72c2a.shtml|website=Il Resto del Carlino|language=it|date=18 July 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Milan-Bologna 5–1, dominio rossonero: solo Ibrahimovic non ride|url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/serie-a/2020/07/18/news/milan-bologna_5-1_dominio_rossonero_ma_ibra_non_gradisce_il_cambio-262319107/|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=18 July 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> In a follow–up match against [[Atalanta B.C.|Atalanta]], Tomiyasu suffered a hamstring injury and was substituted in the 74th minute, as the club loss 1–0.<ref>{{cite news|title=Atalanta-Bologna 1–0: ritorno al successo per i bergamaschi e secondo posto|url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/serie-a/2020/07/21/news/atalanta-bologna_1-0_ritorno_al_successo_bergamaschi_al_secondo_posto-262567117/|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=21 July 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> After the match, it was announced that he would be sidelined for the rest of the 2019–20 season.<ref>{{cite news|title="Quant'è bravo Paz" Ma poi finisce al Lecce|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2020/02/01/quante-bravo-paz-ma-poi-finisce-al-lecceBologna10.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=1 February 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Bologna, Tomiyasu fuori per due settimane|url=https://www.corrieredellosport.it/news/calcio/serie-a/bologna/2020/07/23-72090455/bologna_tomiyasu_fuori_per_due_settimane|website=Corriere Dello Sport|language=it|date=23 July 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Cittadino Mihajlovic per Bologna un onore ma c'è chi dice no|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2020/07/28/cittadino-mihajlovic-per-bologna-un-onore-ma-ce-chi-dice-noBologna13.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=28 July 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> Despite this, Tomiyasu finished his first season at Bologna, making 30 appearances and scoring once in all competitions.<ref>{{cite news|title=セリエA終幕 得点王は36ゴールのインモービレ、1年目冨安は29試合出場、麻也は半年で14試合出場 |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?307367-307367-fl |work=Web Gekisaka |language=ja|date=3 August 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref>

Ahead of the 2020–21 season, Tomiyasu's performances last season led to suggestions that he could be playing in the centre–back position.<ref>{{cite news |date=15 August 2020 |title=Terzino o al centro Tomiyasu ideale in difesa |url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2020/08/15/terzino-o-al-centro-tomiyasu-ideale-in-difesaRoma13.html |access-date=13 August 2021 |website=La Repubblica |language=it}}<br />{{cite news |date=19 August 2020 |title=Dal reparto difensivo più dolori che gioie Riparte la caccia a un centrale |url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2020/08/19/dal-reparto-difensivo-piu-dolori-che-gioie-riparte-la-centraleBologna12.html |access-date=13 August 2021 |website=La Repubblica |language=it}}<br />{{cite news |date=7 September 2020 |title=Bologna, la chiave per la difesa è Tomiyasu centrale |url=https://www.corrieredellosport.it/news/calcio/serie-a/bologna/2020/09/07-73517381/bologna_la_chiave_per_la_difesa_e_tomiyasu_centrale/ |access-date=13 August 2021 |website=Corriere Dello Sport |language=it}}</ref> Tomiyasu soon recovered from his injury and regained his first-team place, playing at centre back.<ref>{{cite news|title=Supryaga in attesa ma Orsolini è già da Mancini|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2020/08/30/supryaga-in-attesa-ma-orsolini-e-gia-da-manciniBologna11.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=30 August 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Bologna, Tomiyasu all'esame Ibrahimovic|url=https://www.corrieredellosport.it/news/calcio/serie-a/bologna/2020/09/18-73901653/bologna_tomiyasu_all_esame_ibrahimovic|website=Corriere Dello Sport|language=it|date=18 September 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Mbaye e Sansone quasi un mese ko Rossoblù contati contro il Napoli|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2020/11/04/mbaye-e-sansone-quasi-un-mese-ko-rossoblu-contati-contro-il-napoliBologna13.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=4 November 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Il Bologna cerca il tris Mihajlovic stuzzica Barrow|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2020/12/05/il-bologna-cerca-il-tris-mihajlovic-stuzzica-barrowBologna12.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=5 December 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Il Bologna si muove per accontentare Mihajlovic|url=https://www.corrieredellosport.it/news/calcio/serie-a/bologna/2020/12/07-77144970/il_bologna_si_muove_per_accontentare_mihajlovic|website=Corriere Dello Sport|language=it|date=7 December 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> In a match against [[U.S. Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]] on 18 October 2020, he scored an own goal after a cross from [[Giorgos Kyriakopoulos]], leading to the winning goal for the opposition team.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bologna-Sassuolo 3–4, la rimonta neroverde vale il secondo posto|url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/serie-a/2020/10/18/news/bologna_sassuolo_partita-270998696/|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=18 October 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> In December, Tomiyasu began playing at right back for the rest of the season, though he occasionally played as a [[left back]] and centre back.<ref>{{cite news|title=Barrow la fa, poi la disfa: 2–2 a La Spezia|url=https://corrieredibologna.corriere.it/bologna/bologna-calcio/20_dicembre_16/barrow-fa-poi-disfa-2-2-la-spezia-dbdbe46a-3fef-11eb-b35a-c646b4c09e29.shtml|website=Corriere Di Bologna|language=it|date=16 December 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Un punto prezioso inaugura l'anno Finisce 0–0 il derby dell'Appennino |url=https://corrieredibologna.corriere.it/bologna/bologna-calcio/21_gennaio_03/punto-prezioso-inaugura-l-anno-finisce-0-0-derby-dell-appennino-6cf68288-4dde-11eb-addc-37a4abced27b.shtml|website=Corriere Di Bologna|language=it|date=3 January 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Il Bologna frena il Verona: 1–0, arriva la prima vittoria dell'anno nuovo|url=https://corrieredibologna.corriere.it/bologna/bologna-calcio/21_gennaio_16/bologna-frena-verona-1-0-arriva-prima-vittoria-dell-anno-nuovo-9d304c4c-5813-11eb-9534-2d1db76ab6b0.shtml|website=Corriere Di Bologna|language=it|date=16 January 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> This was due to his struggles playing at centre back, resulting in criticism by the Italian media.<ref>{{cite news|title=冨安健洋は「CBとしてはもっと成長が必要」 ボローニャ元主将のOB語る|url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2020/10/31/post395595/|website=Football Channel|language=ja|date=31 October 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Quaranta volte senza difesa "Ora chiudete"|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2020/11/16/quaranta-volte-senza-difesa-ora-chiudeteBologna10.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=16 November 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Skorupski decisivo Danilo più vispo di Tomi|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2020/11/30/skorupski-decisivo-danilo-piu-vispo-di-tomiBologna03.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=30 November 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=冨安健洋、ボール奪取数は今季セリエAで現在1位。複数ポジションで貢献|url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2020/12/27/post403867/|website=Football Channel|language=ja|date=27 December 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=冨安健洋の超絶技巧にセリエA公式が注目。ローマ戦で披露した"ソンブレロ" |url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2020/12/28/post404106/ |website=Football Channel|language=ja|date=28 December 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> His performances began to improve as a result of the tactical change.<ref>{{cite news|title=Skorupski para Tomiyasu vigila Soriano domina|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2021/01/17/skorupski-para-tomiyasu-vigila-soriano-dominaBologna12.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=17 January 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Parma-Bologna, derby da salvezza anche per chi sognava un'altra corsa|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2021/02/07/parma-bologna-derby-da-salvezza-anche-per-corsaBologna11.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=7 February 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Bologna, Tomiyasu jolly da blindare|url=https://www.corrieredellosport.it/news/stadio/bologna/2021/02/11-79025885/bologna_tomiyasu_jolly_da_blindare|website=Corriere Dello Sport|language=it|date=11 February 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=E poi ci sarebbe una partita Mihajlovic ripesca Orsolini per la sfida al Sassuolo|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2021/02/20/e-poi-ci-sarebbe-una-partita-mihajlovic-sassuoloBologna14.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=20 February 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Sinisa pronto a sfidare la "sua" Lazio: "Servirà aggressività"|url=https://corrieredibologna.corriere.it/bologna/bologna-calcio/21_febbraio_26/sinisa-pronto-sfidare-sua-lazio-servira-aggressivita-0a858430-781f-11eb-b4a5-af5ff9df46f1.shtml|website=Corriere Di Bologna|language=it|date=21 February 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title="Mihajlovic ha le spalle larghe per proteggere il suo Bologna"|url=https://corrieredibologna.corriere.it/bologna/bologna-calcio/21_marzo_01/mihajlovic-ha-spalle-larghe-proteggere-suo-bologna-9ac2eac8-7a6e-11eb-b2a0-a306c75220e1.shtml|website=Corriere Di Bologna|language=it|date=1 March 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> Tomiyasu  scored his first goal of the season in a 2–2 draw against Atalanta on 23 December.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bologna-Atalanta 2–2: doppio Muriel non basta, Tomiyasu e Paz firmano la rimonta rossoblù|url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/serie-a/2020/12/23/news/bologna_atalanta_pareggio-279693774/|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=23 December 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> Two weeks later on 6 January 2021, he scored his second goal of the season, scoring from a header, in a 2–2 draw against [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Bologna-Udinese 2–2, Arslan al 92' salva i bianconeri|url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/serie-a/bologna/2021/01/06/news/bologna_udinese_pareggio-281389343/|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=6 January 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Piccoli eroismi e comiche finali era ormai fatta ma il pari è giusto|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2021/01/07/piccoli-eroismi-e-comiche-finali-era-ormai-fatta-ma-giustoBologna12.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=7 January 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> However, Tomiyasu suffered a calf injury that saw him out for two weeks.<ref>{{cite news|title=Tomiyasu fuori però torna Dijks De Rossi è venuto a studiare Sinisa|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2021/02/26/tomiyasu-fuori-pero-torna-dijks-de-rossi-e-sinisaBologna15.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=26 February 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Mihajlovic ritrova la "sua" Lazio: "Sfida aperta. Tomiyasu out? Gliel'avete tirata!"|url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Bologna/26-02-2021/bologna-mihajlovic-ritrova-sua-lazio-sfida-aperta-4001016679923.shtml|website=La Gazzetta Dello Sport|language=it|date=26 February 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Bologna, Tomiyasu ko. Mihajlovic: "Gliel'avete tirata per tre settimane... perdiamo tanto"|url=https://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/serie-a/bologna-tomiyasu-ko-mihajlovic-gliel-avete-tirata-per-tre-settimane-perdiamo-tanto-1501063|website=Tutto Mercato Web|language=it|date=26 February 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> He made his return to the starting line–up two weeks later than expected on 14 March against [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]], starting in a 3–1 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bologna-Sampdoria 3–1: i rossoblù si mettono al sicuro|url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/serie-a/2021/03/14/news/bologna_sampdoria_3-1-292206043/|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=14 March 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> His return was short–lived when he suffered a muscular problem against [[Inter Milan]] on 4 April.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bologna-Inter 0–1: decide Lukaku, scudetto sempre più vicino|url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/serie-a/2021/04/03/news/bologna-inter_0-1_decide_lukaku_scudetto_sempre_piu_vicino-295008829/|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=3 April 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Tomiyasu ko, Mihajlovic sbotta: "Anche contro la Mongolia doveva giocare..."|url=https://www.goal.com/it/notizie/tomiyasu-ko-mihajlovic-sbotta-anche-contro-la-mongolia/z8e1lshh5sqb13z4o8yvrwzm5|website=Goal (website)|language=it|date=3 April 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> After being sidelined for a month, he made his return to the starting line–up on 2 May against [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] and played 76 minutes before being substituted, in a 3–3 draw.<ref>{{cite news|title=Miha ripensa alla manita: "Colpa mia. Ma oggi siamo cambiati"|url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Bologna/10-04-2021/roma-bologna-parole-mihajlovic-conferenza-stampa-41032406279.shtml|website=La Gazzetta Dello Sport|language=it|date=10 April 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Col Torino Tomiyasu non recupera|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2021/04/19/col-torino-tomiyasu-non-recuperaBologna11.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=19 April 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Mihajlovic: "Sempre questi rigori contro di noi... E la partita è finita lì"|url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Bologna/25-04-2021/atalanta-bologna-mihajlovic-sempre-questi-rigori-contro-noie-partita-finita-li-410479318329.shtml|website=La Gazzetta Dello Sport|language=it|date=25 April 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Dall'infermeria alla tribuna I dubbi dei dirigenti sulla stagione no|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2021/04/28/dallinfermeria-alla-tribuna-i-dubbi-dei-noBologna11.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=28 April 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=Bologna-Fiorentina 3–3, storico Palacio: tripletta più vecchia della storia della A|url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/serie-a/bologna/2021/05/02/news/bologna_fiorentina_pari-299090644/|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=2 May 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> By the end of the season, he had made 33 appearances and scoring two times in all competitions.

Ahead of the 2021–22 season, Tomiyasu was linked with a move to [[Premier League]] club [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] and Atalanta.<ref>{{cite news |last=Dalla Vite |first=Matteo |date=1 June 2021 |title=Asse Bologna-Atalanta: Barrow da riscattare, Tomiyasu può partire |url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Calciomercato/Bologna/01-06-2021/calciomercato-bologna-atalanta-barrow-tomiyasu-4101510863525.shtml |access-date=13 August 2021 |website=La Gazzetta Dello Sport |language=it}}<br />{{cite news |date=27 June 2021 |title=Atalanta, concorrenza inglese per Tomiyasu: sul giapponese c'è il Tottenham |url=https://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/serie-a/atalanta-concorrenza-inglese-per-tomiyasu-sul-giapponese-c-e-il-tottenham-1552320 |access-date=13 August 2021 |website=Tutto Mercato Web |language=it}}<br />{{cite news |date=27 June 2021 |title=Tottenham open talks to sign Bologna and Japan defender Takehiro Tomiyasu |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11675/12343541/tottenham-open-talks-to-sign-bologna-and-japan-defender-takehiro-tomiyasu |access-date=13 August 2021 |website=Sky Sports}}</ref> Amid the transfer speculation, he made his only appearance of the season against Atalanta, coming on as an 81st-minute substitute, in a 0–0 draw on 28 August 2021.<ref>{{cite news |date=28 August 2021 |title=Atalanta-Bologna 0–0: i nerazzurri non abbattono il muro di Mihajlovic |url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/serie-a/2021/08/28/news/atalanta-bologna_0-0_resiste_il_fortino_di_mihajlovic-315686335/ |access-date=4 September 2021 |website=La Repubblica}}</ref>

===Arsenal===
[[File:RC Lens - Arsenal FC (03-10-2023) 29.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Takehiro Tomiyasu in 2023 with Arsenal.]]

On 31 August 2021, Tomiyasu joined [[Premier League]] side [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] on a four-year deal, with an option for a fifth.<ref>{{cite news|title=Takehiro Tomiyasu: Arsenal agree £19.8m deal for Bologna defender |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/12040/12395735/arsenal-transfer-news-hector-bellerin-set-to-join-real-betis-on-loan-as-gunners-push-for-takehiro-tomiyasu |work=SkySports |date=31 August 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Ames |first=Nick |date=20 March 2024 |title='Dedicate my life for Arsenal': Takehiro Tomiyasu signs new contract to 2026 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2024/mar/20/arsenal-takehiro-tomiyasu-signs-new-contract |access-date=11 April 2025 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> The transfer was variously reported as £15.5 million, £16&nbsp;million and £17&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ornstein |first=David |date=31 August 2021 |title=Arsenal sign Bologna's Takehiro Tomiyasu for £16m |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4201232/2021/08/31/arsenal-sign-bolognas-takehiro-tomiyasu-for-16m/ |access-date=4 September 2021 |website=The New York Times |issn=0362-4331 }}<br />{{cite news|title=Arsenal sign £15.5m Takehiro Tomiyasu and loan Héctor Bellerín to Betis|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/aug/31/arsenal-agree-17m-deal-to-sign-bologna-defender-takehiro-tomiyasu|website=The Guardian|date=31 August 2021|access-date=4 September 2021}}<br />{{Cite news |title=Arsenal sign defender Takehiro Tomiyasu from Bologna |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/takehiro-tomiyasu-arsenal-transfer-news-b1912109.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240623143333/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/takehiro-tomiyasu-arsenal-transfer-news-b1912109.html |archive-date=23 June 2024 |date=31 August 2021 |access-date=4 September 2021 |work=The Independent |language=en-GB |url-status=live }}</ref> Upon joining the club, both manager [[Mikel Arteta]] and technical director [[Edu (footballer, born 1978)|Edu]] commented about the player, describing him as an "important member of the squad" at Arsenal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/welcome-takehiro-tomiyasu-signs-arsenal|title=Welcome Takehiro!: Tomiyasu signs for Arsenal|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|date=31 August 2021|access-date=4 September 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210901195845/https://www.arsenal.com/news/welcome-takehiro-tomiyasu-signs-arsenal|archive-date=1 September 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> He became the fourth Japanese player to sign for the club after [[Junichi Inamoto]] and [[Ryo Miyaichi]]; others such as [[Takuma Asano]] never featured in a competitive senior fixture for Arsenal.<ref>{{cite web |last=Jayaram |first=Shamanth |date=11 September 2021 |title=Five interesting facts about Arsenal new boy Takehiro Tomiyasu |url=https://www.arsenalinsider.com/features/five-interesting-facts-about-arsenal-new-boy-takehiro-tomiyasu/ |access-date=30 November 2023 |website=Arsenal Insider |language=en-GB}}</ref>

On 11 September, he made his first appearance for Arsenal against [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] in a 1–0 win.<ref>{{cite web |last=Jones |first=Lewis |date=11 September 2021 |title=Arsenal 1–0 Norwich: Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang settles the nerves in edgy victory for Mikel Arteta |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/arsenal-vs-norwich-city/report/446318 |access-date=12 September 2021}}</ref> After the match, Tomiyasu's debut performance at the club was praised by manager Arteta and local newspaper, Football London.<ref>{{cite news|title=Arsenal player ratings vs Norwich as Odegaard shines while Tomiyasu impresses on debut|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/arsenal-player-ratings-norwich-tomiyasu-21545661|website=Football London|date=11 September 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/ >{{cite news|title=Every word Mikel Arteta said on Ramsdale vs Leno, Tomiyasu's debut and reception from fans|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/mikel-arteta-ramsdale-leno-tomiyasu-21546319|website=Football London|date=11 September 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> He was named the Arsenal's Player of the Month for September 2021, with 51% of the vote.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/tomiyasu-our-september-player-month|title=Tomiyasu is our September Player of the Month|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|date=7 October 2021|access-date=11 November 2021|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20211007131327/https://www.arsenal.com/news/tomiyasu-our-september-player-month|archive-date=7 October 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> Since joining Arsenal, Tomiyasu became the club's first choice right–back position over from fellow right–back [[Cédric Soares]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Mikel Arteta admits crucial Takehiro Tomiyasu attribute was major factor in Arsenal transfer|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/mikel-arteta-takehiro-tomiyasu-arsenal-21606772|website=Football London|date=18 September 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=Mikel Arteta's £17m masterstroke has unlocked the major threat of Arsenal's key tactical weapon|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/arteta-saka-tomiyasu-arsenal-unlock-21955463|website=Football London|date=25 October 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Edu masterstroke set to save Arsenal over £48m by promoting Takehiro Tomiyasu back-up|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/transfer-news/edu-masterstroke-set-save-arsenal-22081884|website=Football London|date=7 November 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=Mikel Arteta can seal dream Arsenal squad with £32.5m move if Edu makes three transfer decisions|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/fixtures-results/mikel-arteta-edu-arsenal-transfer-22148139|website=Football Londom|date=12 November 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=Edu and Arsenal on red alert as Xavi's Barcelona 'fire sale' can help seal £81m double transfer|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/transfer-news/de-jong-dest-arsenal-transfers-22426827|website=Football London|date=11 December 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> He quickly also became a fan favourite among Arsenal supporters.<ref>{{cite news|title=The key attribute that makes Arsenal fans love Takehiro Tomiyasu|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/takehiro-tomiyasu-arsenal-mikel-arteta-21813681|website=Football London|date=10 October 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> Following a 2–0 win against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] on 30 October, manager Arteta praised his impact to the team and his settling to the country.<ref>{{cite news|title=What Martin Odegaard did to help Takehiro Tomiyasu before Arsenal debut|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/players/martin-odegaard-takehiro-tomiyasu-arsenal-21695585|website=Football London|date=28 September 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/arteta-ramsdale-win-tomiyasu-and-more|title= Arteta on Ramsdale, the win, Tomiyasu and more|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|date=30 October 2021|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240227092117/https://www.arsenal.com/news/arteta-ramsdale-win-tomiyasu-and-more|archive-date=27 February 2024|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite news|title=Arsenal fans spotted what Takehiro Tomiyasu did to Jamie Vardy during 2–0 win over Leicester|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/tomiyasu-arsenal-jamie-vardy-leicester-22022614|website=Football London|date=31 October 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> During a 4–1 win against [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] on 18 December, Tomiyasu suffered a muscle injury and was substituted in the 64th minute.<ref>{{cite news|title=Leeds 1–4 Arsenal: Gabriel Martinelli scores twice in Gunners win|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59618480|website=BBC Sport|date=18 December 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/ >{{cite news|title=Every word Mikel Arteta said on Martinelli's display, Arsenal's COVID cases and racist abuse|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/fixtures-results/mikel-arteta-martinelli-covid-racism-22509058|website=Football London|date=18 December 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=Arsenal injury and Covid news: Latest updates on Takehiro Tomiyasu and Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/players/tomiyasu-aubameyang-arsenal-injury-news-22525966|website=Football London|date=23 December 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> After missing one match, he returned from injury, starting a match, in a 2–1 loss against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] on 1 January 2022.<ref>{{cite news|title=Arsenal 1–2 Manchester City: Rodri scores late winner|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59787808|website=BBC Sport|date=1 January 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> After the match, Football London, once again, praised Tomiyasu's performance on his return.<ref>{{cite news|title=Arsenal player ratings vs Manchester City as Odegaard shines while Tomiyasu and Partey star|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/fixtures-results/arsenal-ratings-odegaard-tomiyasu-partey-22621862|website=Football London|date=1 January 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> However, his return was short–lived when he suffered two separate injuries that saw him out until April.<ref>{{cite news|title=Smith Rowe, Xhaka, Gabriel: Arsenal injury and Covid news ahead of Liverpool Carabao Cup clash|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/arsenal-injury-liverpool-smith-rowe-22694976|website=Football London|date=10 January 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/ >{{cite news|title=Tomiyasu absent, Odegaard returns as wonderkids called up to Arsenal training ahead of Liverpool|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/tomiyasu-odegaard-arsenal-training-liverpool-22805615|website=Football London|date=19 January 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/ >{{cite news|title=Mikel Arteta's decisions hint at Takehiro Tomiyasu replacement for Arsenal against Wolves|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/players/arsenal-tomiyasu-replacement-wolves-arteta-23021726|website=Football London|date=8 February 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/ >{{cite news|title=Medical expert hands Arsenal Takehiro Tomiyasu injury update triggering major Liverpool decision|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/arsenal-injury-update-tomiyasu-liverpool-23222944|website=Football London|date=26 February 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/ >{{cite news|title=Mikel Arteta can continue Arsenal approach to make easy Takehiro Tomiyasu decision vs Liverpool|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/players/tomiyasu-arsenal-mikel-arteta-liverpool-23396523|website=Football London|date=16 March 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> He made his return from injury, coming on as a late substitute, in a 3–1 win against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] on 23 April.<ref>{{cite news|title=Arsenal 3–1 Manchester United: Granit Xhaka seals win as Gunners stay fourth in Champions League race|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/61125048|website=BBC Sport|date=23 April 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> Following this, Tomiyasu was able to make three starts in the next three matches.<ref>{{cite news|title=West Ham United 1–2 Arsenal: Gunners reclaim Champions League place|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/61205838|website=BBC Sport|date=1 May 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/ >{{cite news|title=Arsenal predicted XI vs Leeds as Eddie Nketiah targets revenge and Takehiro Tomiyasu continues|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/fixtures-results/arsenal-leeds-eddie-nketiah-tomiyasu-23885676|website=Football London|date=8 May 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/ >{{cite news|title=Arsenal 2–1 Leeds United: Gunners take control of top-four race|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/61288436|website=BBC Sport|date=8 May 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/ >{{cite news|title=Mikel Arteta has three Arsenal players to win key battles in North London Derby vs Tottenham|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/fixtures-results/north-london-derby-tottenham-arsenal-23915116|website=Football London|date=10 May 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=Arsenal player ratings vs Tottenham as Rob Holding loses head but Takehiro Tomiyasu impresses|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/fixtures-results/arsenal-tottenham-rob-holding-tomiyasu-23944612|website=Football London|date=12 May 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref>  However during a 2–0 loss against [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] on 16 May, he suffered a hamstring injury and was substituted in the 39th minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2022-May-16/newcastle-united-2-0-arsenal-match-report|title=Match report: Newcastle United 2–0 Arsenal|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|date=16 May 2022|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220516221434/https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2022-May-16/newcastle-united-2-0-arsenal-match-report|archive-date=16 May 2022|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite news|title=Arsenal handed major injury blow as Takehiro Tomiyasu forced off vs Newcastle|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/tomiyasu-injury-newcastle-arsenal-breaking-23976572|website=Football London|date=16 May 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/ >{{cite news|title=Arsenal confirm Takehiro Tomiyasu hamstring injury as Mikel Arteta names starting XI for Everton|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/players/arsenal-everton-lineup-takehiro-tomiyasu-24029867|website=Football London|date=22 May 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> At the end of the 2021–22 season, Tomiyasu made 22 appearances in all competitions.

At the start of the 2022–23 season, Tomiyasu lost his place in the right–back to [[Ben White (footballer)|Ben White]] when [[William Saliba]] returned on loan.<ref>{{cite news|title=Takehiro Tomiyasu's new role hinted at as Mikel Arteta 'targets' Arsenal right-back transfer|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/transfer-news/takehrio-tomiyasu-arteta-arsenal-transfer-23798577|website=Football London|date=27 April 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/ >{{cite news|title= What Mikel Arteta said to William Saliba before Palace masterclass as Arsenal show development|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/fixtures-results/william-saliba-mikel-arteta-arsenal-24687567|website=Football London|date=6 August 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}< br/>{{cite news|title=Takehiro Tomiyasu explains Arsenal role after losing starting spot to Ben White|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/arsenal-fc-news-tomiyasu-white-b1030957.html|website=Evening Standard|date=8 September 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/ >{{cite news|title=Takehiro Tomiyasu 'not satisfied' with Arsenal role and sends huge Ben White warning message|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/tomiyasu-arsenal-role-white-warning-25093519|website=Football London|date=23 September 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}< br/>{{cite news|title=Takehiro Tomiyasu doubles down on his Ben White Arsenal battle amid major Liverpool prediction|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/takehiro-tomiyasu-doubles-down-ben-25203737|website=Football London|date=7 October 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> He made his first start of the season, in a 2–1 win against [[FC Zürich]] in the [[UEFA Europa League]] match on 8 September.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2022-Sep-08/fc-zurich-1-2-arsenal-match-report|title=Report: FC Zurich 1–2 Arsenal|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|date=8 September 2022|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220908195515/https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2022-Sep-08/fc-zurich-1-2-arsenal-match-report|archive-date=8 September 2022|url-status=live}}</ref> Following the injury of [[Oleksandr Zinchenko (footballer)|Oleksandr Zinchenko]], Tomiyasu started in the left–back position against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] and helped Arsenal win 3–2.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2022-Oct-09/arsenal-3-2-liverpool-match|title=Match report: Arsenal 3–2 Liverpool|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|date=9 October 2022|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20221009183915/https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2022-Oct-09/arsenal-3-2-liverpool-match|archive-date=9 October 2022|url-status=live}}<br/ >{{cite news|title=Martinelli, Saka and Arteta's biggest critics – Arsenal winners and losers after Liverpool winl|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/martinelli-saka-arteta-arsenal-liverpool-25218771|website=Football London|date=10 October 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/ >{{cite news|title=Saliba shines, Jesus conflicts – Arsenal Premier League player ratings so far this season|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/arsenal-player-ratings-saliba-jesus-25515089|website=Football London|date=15 November 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> He started in the next three matches, playing in the left–back position for the club.<ref>{{cite news|title=Takehiro Tomiyasu's Leeds selection and the Arsenal tactical question Mikel Arteta must answer|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/leeds-arsenal-takehiro-tomiyasu-arteta-25266180|website=Football London|date=14 October 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/ >{{cite news|title=Ramsdale shines, Tomiyasu struggles and Arsenal battle – Winners and losers from 1–0 Leeds win|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/ramsdale-tomiyasu-arsenal-leeds-win-25278289|website=Football London|date=17 October 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/ >{{cite news|title=Why Mikel Arteta prefers Takehiro Tomiyasu at left-back and Thomas Partey role will come next|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/mikel-arteta-tomiyasu-partey-arsenal-25405833|website=Football London|date=1 November 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> However, Tomiyasu suffered a muscle injury, having came on as 73rd-minute substitute and came off 15 minutes later, in a 1–0 win against FC Zürich on 3 November.<ref>{{cite news|title=Arsenal boss Mikel Arteta provides Takehiro Tomiyasu injury update amid Chelsea doubt|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/fixtures-results/mikel-arteta-arsenal-chelsea-aubameyang-25431394|website=Football London|date=3 November 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> Following the World Cup, he found himself behind pecking the order, with White and Zinchenko preferred as Arsenal's first–choice full–backs.<ref>{{cite news|title=Arsenal's three immediate William Saliba replacements for Newcastle clash as double risk emerges|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/arsenal-william-saliba-replacements-newcastle-25878669|website=Football London|date=3 January 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/ >{{cite news|title=Mikel Arteta told to make Ben White decision as Arsenal dilemma looms ahead of Brentford|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/players/ben-white-arsenal-mikel-arteta-26172151|website=Football London|date=7 February 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/ >{{cite news|title=Saka, White, Odegaard, Gabriel and Saliba all superb – Arsenal 2022/23 players ratings so far|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/arsenal-player-ratings-saka-odegaard-26535897|website=Football London|date=23 March 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref>

In a match against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] on 22 January 2023, Tomiyasu came on as a second–half substitute and played a role when he set up a goal for [[Bukayo Saka]] to take a 2–1 lead, as the club won 3–1.<ref>{{cite news |title=Arsenal 3–2 Manchester United: Late goal by Eddie Nketiah gives Arsenal win over United |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/64279776 |website=BBC Sport |date=22 January 2023 |access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> Three week later on 15 February 2023 against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], Tomiyasu started the match and was at fault when he made a "poor backpass allowed [[Kevin de Bruyne]] to loft a finish over [[Aaron Ramsdale]] after 24 minutes", as Arsenal loss 3–1.<ref>{{cite news |title=Arsenal 1–3 Manchester City: Pep Guardiola's side go top with victory at Emirates |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63224218 |website=BBC Sport |date=15 February 2023 |access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> After the match, [[Evening Standard|London Evening Standard]] and Football London both described his performance as "poor".<ref>{{cite news|title=Arsenal player ratings vs Manchester City as Jorginho superb but Tomiyasu and Gabriel poor|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/fixtures-results/arsenal-player-ratings-manchester-city-26250505|website=Football London|date=13 February 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Arsenal player ratings vs Man City: Gabriel and Takehiro Tomiyasu with huge errors; Martin Odegaard struggles|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/arsenal-player-ratings-vs-man-city-gabriel-tomiyasu-odegaard-b1060690.html|website=Evening Standard|date=15 February 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Arteta's substitution problem, Man United – Winners and losers from Arsenal's Man City defeat|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/fixtures-results/arsenal-man-city-arteta-problem-26250920|website=Football London|date=16 February 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> However, he sustained a knee injury and was substituted in the 9th minute during Arsenal's loss against [[Sporting CP]] in the second leg of the UEFA Europa League last 16.<ref>{{cite news|title=Arsenal hit by Takehiro Tomiyasu injury dilemma during clash vs Sporting CP|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/breaking-arsenal-hit-takehiro-tomiyasu-26491936|website=Football London|date=16 March 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> After the match, it was announced that Tomiyasu was out for the rest of the 2022–23 season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Takehiro Tomiyasu return date revealed following major Arsenal injury blow|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/takehiro-tomiyasu-return-arsenal-injury-26528816|website=Football London|date=22 March 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> At the end of the 2022–23 season, he made 31 appearances in all competitions.

Ahead of the 2023–24 season, Tomiyasu spent Arsenal's remainder pre–season friendly tour recuperating.<ref>{{cite news|title=William Saliba returns, Gabriel Martinelli boost – Things spotted in Arsenal pre-season training|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/saliba-injury-martinelli-arsenal-training-27255641|website=Football London|date=4 July 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Why Martin Odegaard is not in Arsenal squad vs Nurnberg and five other absences explained|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/fixtures-results/martin-odegaard-not-arsenal-squad-27317606|website=Football London|date=13 July 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Takehiro Tomiyasu on injury recovery, losing confidence, versatility and Arsenal training|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/players/takehiro-tomiyasu-injury-recovery-losing-27394291|website=Football London|date=25 July 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> He made his first appearance since returning from injury, coming on as a 50th-minute substitute, in a 2–1 win against [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] in the first game of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2023-Aug-12/arsenal-2-1-nottingham-forest-fc-match-report|title=Report: Arsenal 2–1 Nottingham Forest|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|date=12 August 2023|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20230813160338/https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2023-Aug-12/arsenal-2-1-nottingham-forest-fc-match-report|archive-date=13 August 2023|url-status=live}}</ref> However on 21 August 2023, Tomiyasu made his first start of the 2023–24 season, in Arsenal's 1–0 win at [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]], where he was controversially sent off in the 67th minute for two bookable offences.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66495070|website=BBC Sport|title=Odegaard penalty gives Arsenal win at Crystal Palace|first=Emlyn|last=Begley|date=21 August 2023|access-date=21 August 2023}}</ref> Following his return from suspension, Tomiyasu continued to rotate playing in either left–back or right–back position.<ref>{{cite news|title=Arsenal have a new problem as £19.8m alternative highlights issue in absence of Jurrien Timber|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/arsenal-new-problem-198m-alternative-27843318|website=Football London|date=5 October 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Arsenal have found the perfect blend with Oleksandr Zinchenko and Takehiro Tomiyasu|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/arsenal-takehiro-tomiyasu-oleksandr-zinchenko-27980287|website=Football London|date=26 October 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Arsenal have popular Takehiro Tomiyasu decision and Kai Havertz U-turn to consider vs Newcastle|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/fixtures-results/kai-havertz-uturn-arsenal-newcastle-28045161|website=Football London|date=4 November 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> On 27 September, Tomiyasu was finally used as a centre back for Arsenal in the [[2023–24 EFL Cup]] third round match against [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]] and contributed to a 1–0 clean sheet victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2023-Sep-27/brentford-arsenal-match-report|title=Report: Brentford 0–1 Arsenal|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|date=27 September 2023|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20230927211317/https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2023-Sep-27/brentford-arsenal-match-report|archive-date=27 September 2023|url-status=live}}</ref>

A week later on 8 October against Manchester City, he came on as a 75th-minute substitute, and was involved in a goal that led to [[Gabriel Martinelli]] to score the only goal of the game.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2023-Oct-08/arsenal-1-0-manchester-city-match-report|title=Report: Arsenal 1–0 Manchester City|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|date=8 October 2023|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20231010040352/https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2023-Oct-08/arsenal-1-0-manchester-city-match-report|archive-date=10 October 2023|url-status=live}}</ref> Three weeks later on 28 October, Tomiyasu scored his first goal for the club in the 96th minute of stoppage time in a 5–0 victory over [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Thomas|first=Marissa|title=Arsenal 5–0 Sheffield United|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67179271|work=BBC Sport|date=28 October 2023}}</ref> After the match, he dedicated his goal to his mother, who died the previous year.<ref>{{cite news|title=Takehiro Tomiyasu sends emotional message after scoring first Arsenal goal vs Sheffield United|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/takehiro-tomiyasu-emotional-arsenal-united-28004268 |website=Football London|date=29 October 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> On 2 November, Tomiyasu was selected as the team's monthly MVP for October by fan voting, making it his second award since September 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2 November 2023|title=Takehiro Tomiyasu's excellent displays during October have seen our supporters vote him as our men's Player of the Month.|url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/tomiyasu-october-men-player-month|access-date=2 November 2023|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20231102233135/https://www.arsenal.com/news/tomiyasu-october-men-player-month|archive-date=2 November 2023|url-status=live}}</ref> He then set up three goals in two consecutive matches between 29 November and 2 December, including assisting twice, in a 6–0 win against [[RC Lens]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2023-Nov-29/arsenal-rc-lens-match-report|title=Report: Arsenal 6–0 RC Lens|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|date=29 November 2023|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20231202054831/https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2023-Nov-29/arsenal-rc-lens-match-report|archive-date=2 December 2023|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2023-Dec-02/arsenal-2-1-wolves-match-report|title=Report: Arsenal 2–1 Wolves|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|date=2 December 2023|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20231203155731/https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2023-Dec-02/arsenal-2-1-wolves-match-report|archive-date=3 December 2023|url-status=live}}</ref> However, Tomiyasu played once between December and March, due to suffering from two separate calf injuries and international commitment.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mikel Arteta hit with Takehiro Tomiyasu injury blow in Arsenal vs Wolves|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/breaking-mikel-arteta-hit-takehiro-28217391|website=Football London|date=2 December 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Arsenal handed injury blow with Takehiro Tomiyasu set for extended spell out|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/fixtures-results/arsenal-handed-injury-blow-takehiro-28239658|website=Football London|date=6 December 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2023-Dec-31/fulham-2-1-arsenal-match-report|title=Report: Fulham 2–1 Arsenal|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|date=31 December 2023|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20231231163756/https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2023-Dec-31/fulham-2-1-arsenal-match-report|archive-date=31 December 2023|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite news|title=Mikel Arteta provides fresh Takehiro Tomiyasu injury update as Arsenal absence explained|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/mikel-arteta-provides-fresh-takehiro-28612588|website=Football London|date=11 February 2024|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=What Takehiro Tomiyasu did in training to show Mikel Arteta he's ready for Arsenal injury return|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/what-takehiro-tomiyasu-training-show-28805506|website=Football London|date=12 March 2024|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref>

On 20 March 2024, Tomiyasu extended his contract with the club until 2026.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68613711|title=Arsenal: Takehiro Tomiyasu signs new contract to 2026|work=BBC Sport|date=20 March 2024}}</ref> Eleven days later on 31 March, he made his return from injury, coming on as a 66th-minute substitute, in a 0–0 draw against Manchester City.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2024-Mar-31/manchester-city-0-0-arsenal-match-report|title=Report: Manchester City 0–0 Arsenal|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|date=31 March 2024|access-date=12 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240401081020/https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2024-Mar-31/manchester-city-0-0-arsenal-match-report|archive-date=1 April 2024|url-status=live}}</ref> Following his return from injury, Tomiyasu soon regained his first team place, playing in the left–back position for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{cite news |date=3 April 2024 |title='I can't tell you' – Oleksandr Zinchenko opens up on Arsenal competition and Mikel Arteta headache |url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/i-cant-tell-you-oleksandr-28934796 |access-date=12 September 2024 |website=Football London}}<br />{{cite news |date=8 May 2024 |title=Mikel Arteta favourite makes Manchester United promise to delight Arsenal fans in title boost |url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/mikel-arteta-favourite-makes-manchester-29130665 |access-date=12 September 2024 |website=Football London}}</ref> In the last game of the season against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]], he scored an equalising goal, just two minutes before half–time, "with a fine low finish from the edge of the area following a pull-back from [[Martin Ødegaard]] ", in a 2–1 win; which saw Arsenal finish second in the league again behind Manchester City.<ref>{{cite news|title=Arsenal 2–1 Everton: Gunners miss out on Premier League|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c0v0vrg7y89t|website=BBC Sport|date=19 May 2024|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br>{{Cite web|last=Olley|first=James|date=20 May 2024|title=The story of Arsenal's season and where they can improve|url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/40183639/the-story-arsenals-premier-league-season-where-improve |access-date=12 September 2024|publisher=ESPN}}</ref> At the end of the 2023–24 season, Tomiyasu made 29 appearances and scoring 2 times in all competitions.

The start of the 2024–25 season saw Tomiyasu out with a knee injury, which he sustained during Arsenal's pre–season tour.<ref>{{cite news|title=Takehiro Tomiyasu Arsenal injury timeline revealed as Mikel Arteta faces major dilemma|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/takehiro-tomiyasu-arsenal-injury-timeline-29584877|website=Football London|date=21 July 2024|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> As a result of his ongoing injury issues, with a further operation required in February 2025, Arsenal and Tomiyasu mutually agreed to terminate his contract in July 2025.<ref>{{Cite news |last=McNicholas |first=James |date=2025-07-04 |title=Takehiro Tomiyasu set to leave Arsenal by mutual consent |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6472981/2025/07/04/takehiro-tomiyasu-leaves-arsenal-transfers/ |access-date=2025-07-04 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>

===Ajax===
On 16 December 2025, [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] announced that it has reached an agreement with Tomiyasu on his move to Amsterdam. This signing makes him only the second Japanese player in the club history, the other being [[Ko Itakura]]. The free-agent defender signed a contract for half a season, running until the end of 2025−26 season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ajax Sign Takehiro Tomiyasu on Short-Term Deal|url=https://www.transferwatcher.com/eredivisie-transfers/ajax-sign-takehiro-tomiyasu-on-short-term-deal|website=Transferwatcher.com|date=16 December 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
[[File:Iran - Japan, AFC Asian Cup 2019 21.jpg|thumb|left|300px|Tomiyasu attempts to clear the ball during the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup knockout stage#Iran vs Japan|semi–finals of the AFC Asian Cup]] against [[Iran national football team|Iran]].]]

Having previously played for Japan U14 and Japan U15,<ref>{{cite news|title=全国3会場で開催される、ナショナルトレセンU-14西日本メンバー発|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?84614-78681-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=16 May 2011|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title=U-14日本選抜 中国遠征1日目試合結果|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?98470-98957-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=26 April 2012|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title=U-15日本代表候補、西日本キャンプメンバー発表…3月14日から広島で開催|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?111285-114487-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=27 February 2013|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title=U-15日本代表、マレーシア遠征メンバーを発表|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?117109-121583-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=11 July 2013|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> Tomiyasu was called up to the Japan U16 for the first time in March 2013 ahead of the [[Montaigu Tournament]].<ref>{{cite news|title=U-16日本代表 フランス遠征メンバーが発表 トッテナムMFサイ・ゴダードも招集|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?111611-114873-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=7 March 2013|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> He participated in the tournament, as the U16 side finished seventh place.<ref>{{cite news|title=U-16代表、杉森の2ゴールでフランスに逆転勝ち|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?112533-116026-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=29 March 2013|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title=チリ完封のU-16日本代表は7位で大会を終える|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?112740-116265-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=2 April 2013|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> In August 2014, Tomiyasu was called for Japan U16 ahead of the [[2014 AFC U-16 Championship|AFC U-16 Championship]] in Thailand.<ref>{{cite news |date=25 August 2014 |title=AFC U－16選手権臨む日本代表発表…4強入りで5大会連続U－17W杯へ |url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20140825/225110.html |access-date=12 September 2024 |publisher=Soccer King |language=ja}}</ref> He made two appearances in the tournament, as Japan U16 were eliminated in the quarter–finals.<ref>{{cite news|title=U-16日本代表 AFC U-16選手権 2連勝でグループステージ突破を決める|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u16/u16_afc/news/00001939/|publisher=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=9 September 2014|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title= [AFC U-16選手権]冨安「この経験があったからこそ成長したんだと、後々言えるようにしたい」|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u16/u16_afc/news/00002016/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=15 September 2014|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref>

In July 2014, Tomiyasu was called up to the [[Japan national under-17 football team|Japan U17]] for the first time.<ref>{{cite news|title=U-17日本代表 国際ユースサッカーin新潟（7/15～21） メンバー・スケジュール|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u17/international_youth_soccer/news/00001213/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=8 July 2014|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title= U-17日本代表 第18回国際ユースサッカーin新潟 初戦のU-17セルビア代表に勝利|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u17/international_youth_soccer/news/00001389/|publisher=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=20 July 2014|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=U-17日本代表 第18回国際ユースサッカーin新潟 U-17メキシコ代表と引き分け準優勝で大会を終える|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/news/00001400/|publisher=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=22 July 2014|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> He participated in a number of matches for the side throughout 2015.<ref>{{cite news|title= U-17日本代表 第11回国際ユーストーナメント（U-17）Inミンスク2015 グループリーグ第2戦vs リトアニア 代表|url=https://www.jfa.jp/news/00004672/|publisher=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=21 January 2015|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=U-17日本代表 サニックス杯 国際ユースサッカー大会 2015 開幕|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u17_2014/news/00005763/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=19 March 2015|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref>

In June 2015, Tomiyasu was called up to the Japan U18 squad for the [[2015 Panda Cup|Panda Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|title=U-18日本代表 中国遠征【Panda Cup 2015】（6/22～29@成都） 選手入れ替えについて|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u18_2015/pandacup2015/news/00006485/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=22 June 2015|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> He played two times in the tournament, as the U18 side won the trophy, finishing first place.<ref>{{cite news|title=U-18日本代表 Panda Cup マッチレポート vs.U-18キルギス代表|url=http://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u18_2015/pandacup2015/news/00006522/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=25 June 2015|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=U-18日本代表 Panda Cup 第3戦マッチレポート vs.U-18スロバキア代表|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u18_2015/pandacup2015/news/00006581/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=29 June 2015|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> In March 2016, Tomiyasu was called up to the [[Japan national under-19 football team|Japan U-19]] squad for the first time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/news/post-2880|title=邦本 宜裕 選手と冨安 健洋 選手が、U-19日本代表 バーレーン遠征のメンバーに選出|publisher=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=15 March 2016|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200418165111/https://www.avispa.co.jp/news/post-2880|archive-date=18 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Six months later, he was called up for the second time by the Japan U19 squad ahead of the [[2016 AFC U-19 Championship|AFC U-19 Championship]] in Bahrain.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/news/post-7165|title=U-19日本代表AFC U-19選手権バーレーン2016のメンバーに 冨安 健洋 選手 選出|publisher=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=28 September 2016|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200418165004/https://www.avispa.co.jp/news/post-7165|archive-date=18 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Tomiyasu played his first match of the tournament, where he helped the U19 side win 3–0 against [[Yemen national under-20 football team|Yemen U19]].<ref>{{cite news|title=エU-19日本代表 AFC U-19選手権バーレーン2016 グループステージ初戦を勝利で飾る！|url=http://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u19_2016/afc_u19_championship_2016/news/00011246/|publisher=Japan Football Association|language=Japanese|date=15 October 2016|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> Tomiyasu scored his first goal of the tournament, in a 3–0 win against [[Qatar national under-20 football team|Qatar U19]] on 20 October 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title= U-19日本代表 AFC U-19選手権バーレーン2016 カタールに勝利し、グループステージ1位突破を決める！|url=http://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u19_2016/afc_u19_championship_2016/news/00011305/|website=Japan Football Association|language=Japanese|date=21 October 2016|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> He helped the Japan U19 reached the final after beating [[Vietnam national under-20 football team|Vietnam]] in the semi–final.<ref>{{cite news|title= U-19日本代表 AFC U-19選手権バーレーン2016 ベトナムに快勝し、決勝への切符を掴む！|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u19_2016/afc_u19_championship_2016/news/00011364/|website=Japan Football Association|language=Japanese|date=28 October 2016|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> Tomiyasu started in the final against [[Saudi Arabia national under-20 football team|Saudi Arabia U19]] and played 120 minutes; which resulting Japan U19 won 5–3 on penalties.<ref name="Tomiyasu 2016 AFC U-19 Championship">{{cite news|title= U-19日本代表 AFC U-19選手権バーレーン2016 PK戦の末、大会初優勝を飾る！|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u19_2016/afc_u19_championship_2016/news/00011380/|publisher=Japan Football Association|language=Japanese|date=31 October 2016|access-date=13 July 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=U19日本、初のアジア王者に！ PK戦でサウジ撃破、全試合無失点で大会制す|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20161031/509597.html|website=Soccer King|language=ja|date=31 October 2016|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{Cite web |title=AFC U-19 Championship 2016 |url=https://www.the-afc.com/afcasfeeds?fixtureid=10334&stageid=407&tMode=C&view=ajax&show=matchsummary |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161101164054/http://www.the-afc.com:80/afcasfeeds?fixtureid=10334&stageid=407&tMode=C&view=ajax&show=matchsummary |archive-date=1 November 2016 |access-date=1 December 2023 |publisher=Asian Football Confederation}}</ref> During the AFC U-19 Championship tournament, he helped the Japan U19 side keep all six clean sheets.<ref>{{cite news|title=U-19日本代表 AFC U-19選手権バーレーン2016 U-19イラン代表との対戦はスコアレスドロー|url=https://www.jfa.jp/news/00011273/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=18 October 2016|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title= U-19日本代表 5大会ぶりとなるFIFA U-20ワールドカップ出場権を獲得！ AFC U-19選手権バーレーン2016|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u19_2016/afc_u19_championship_2016/news/00011339/|website=Japan Football Association|language=Japanese|date=25 October 2016|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref>

In May 2017, Tomiyasu was elected [[Japan national under-20 football team|Japan U-20 national team]] for [[2017 FIFA U-20 World Cup|2017 U-20 World Cup]] in South Korea.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/academy/post-10935|title=FIFA U-20ワールドカップ韓国2017 U-20日本代表メンバーに冨安 健洋 選手 選出のお知らせ|publisher=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=2 May 2017|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200418210148/https://www.avispa.co.jp/academy/post-10935|archive-date=18 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He made his Japan U20 debut, starting the whole game, in a 3–2 win against [[Honduras national under-20 football team|Honduras U-20]] in a friendly match.<ref>{{cite news|title=U-20日本代表 韓国入りを前に3–2でU-20ホンジュラス代表に勝利|url=http://www.jfa.jp/national_team/news/00013513/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=16 May 2017|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> At this tournament, he played full time in all 4 matches as centre back, as the U-20 side were eliminated in the quarter–finals by [[Venezuela national under-20 football team|Venezuela U20]].<ref>{{cite news|title=FIFA U-20ワールドカップ U-20日本代表が南アフリカを下して白星発進|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u20_2017/u20_worldcup2017/news/00013632/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=22 May 2017|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=FIFA U-20ワールドカップ U-20日本代表、ウルグアイに敗れて1勝1敗に|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u20_2017/news/00013660/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=25 May 2017|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br /> {{cite news|title=U－20日本、W杯ベスト16進出！ 堂安が躍動、2点差追いつきイタリアとドロー|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20170527/593289.html|website=Soccer King|language=ja|date=27 May 2017|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=U－20日本代表、延長戦の末にベネズエラに敗戦…5大会ぶりのU－20W杯はベスト16|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20170530/594177.html|website=Soccer King|language=ja|date=30 May 2017|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref>

In May 2018, Tomiyasu was called up to the [[Japan national under-23 football team|Japan U21]] for the first time ahead of the [[2018 Toulon Tournament|Toulon Tournament]].<ref>{{cite news|title=第46回トゥーロン国際大会2018 U-21日本代表メンバー・スケジュール（5/28～6/9）|url=http://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u21_2018/toulontournament_2018/news/00017533/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=15 May 2018|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> He went on to make four appearances for the side, as they were eliminated in the Group stage.<ref>{{cite news|title=U-21日本代表、1–2でトルコ代表に敗れる ～第46回トゥーロン国際大会2018～|url=http://www.jfa.jp/news/00017649/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=28 May 2018|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=U-21日本代表、ポルトガルに逆転勝利で準決勝進出に望みつなぐ～第46回トゥーロン国際大会2018|url=https://www.jfa.jp/news/00017678/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=1 June 2018|access-date=11 August 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=U-21日本代表 カナダに引き分け、準決勝進出はならず ～第46回トゥーロン国際大会2018～|url=http://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u21_2018/news/00017692/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=4 June 2018|access-date=11 August 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=U- U-21日本代表 トーゴに勝利し、7位で大会を終える～第46回トゥーロン国際大会2018～|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u21_2018/toulontournament_2018/news/00017692/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=7 June 2018|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref>

In June 2021, Tomiyasu was named in the [[Japan national under-23 football team|Japan squad]] for his first [[2020 Summer Olympics|Olympic]] [[Football at the 2020 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|tournament]], this time on home soil.<ref>{{Cite web|title=U-24 Japan National Team Squad – Games of the XXXII Olympiad (Tokyo 2020)【7/21-8/7】, KIRIN CHALLENGE CUP 2021【7/12＠Osaka, 7/17＠Hyogo】|url=https://www.jfa.jp/news/00027265/|access-date=13 August 2021|website=JFA｜公益財団法人日本サッカー協会|language=ja}}</ref> He previously expressed his interest in playing at the tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=東京五輪世代のDF冨安健洋 「自分のプレーでチームに貢献するのが大事」|url=https://www.sponichi.co.jp/soccer/news/2021/05/26/kiji/20210526s00002000341000c.html|website=Sponichi Annex|language=ja|date=26 May 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> Prior to the start of the Olympics, Tomiyasu was featured three out of the four friendly matches for the national side.<ref>{{cite news|title=堂安、久保ら攻撃陣が躍動！ ベストメンバーで臨んだU－24日本、ガーナに6発快勝|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20210605/1536928.html|website=Soccer King|language=ja|date=5 June 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=U24日本代表、ホンジュラスに3得点勝利…堂安が2発、東京五輪に向けて弾み|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20210712/1548821.html|website=Soccer King|language=ja|date=12 July 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=U-24日本代表 優勝候補のスペインと引き分け。課題と収穫を得る試合に～キリンチャレンジカップ2021～|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u24_2021/news/00027501/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=18 July 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> Along the way, he suffered ankle injury, but it did not affect his chances to be in the Olympics squad.<ref>{{cite news|title=UＵ24冨安健洋ケガで離脱 ジャマイカ戦、瀬古歩夢を追加招集|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/202106090000396.html|website=Nikkan Sports|language=ja|date=9 June 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=「ここにいることは当たり前じゃない」冨安健洋、東京五輪への強い思い|url=https://www.goal.com/jp/%E3%83%8B%E3%83%A5%E3%83%BC%E3%82%B9/japan-u24-olympic-tomiyasu-2021-07-05/queexi3nhky91efqtgipv4mvw|website=Goal (website)|language=ja|date=5 July 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> Tomiyasu made his debut in the tournament against [[France Olympic football team|France Olympic team]] on 28 July 2021 and started the whole game to help Japan win 4–0.<ref>{{cite news|title= U-24日本代表 フランスに勝利してノックアウトステージ進出|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u24_2021/news/00027600/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=28 July 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> He made two more appearances for the Olympics team, including a 2–0 loss against [[Mexico national under-23 football team|Mexico Olympic team]] in the [[Football at the 2020 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament#Bronze medal match|bronze medal match]].<ref>{{cite news|title=日本、死闘の末に東京五輪4強進出！ PK戦でニュージーランドを下す|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20210731/1554681.html|website=Soccer King|language=ja|date=31 July 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=冨安 銅メダル獲得へ「あとはもう気持ちしかない」|url=https://www.sponichi.co.jp/soccer/news/2021/08/05/kiji/20210805s00002000147000c.html|website=Sponichi Annex|language=ja|date=4 August 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=U-24日本代表 1–3でメキシコに敗れ、東京オリンピックを4位で終える|url=https://www.jfa.jp/news/00027672/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=7 August 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=負傷に出場停止で不完全燃焼…冨安健洋「本当にどうしようもない」|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?338332-338332-fl|website=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=7 August 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref>

===Senior===
[[File:Iran - Japan, AFC Asian Cup 2019 24.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Tomiyasu headed the ball away from [[Sardar Azmoun]] during the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup knockout stage#Iran vs Japan|semi–finals of the AFC Asian Cup]] against [[Iran national football team|Iran]].]]

On 30 August 2018, Tomiyasu received his first international call-up from the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]] for the [[Kirin Cup|Kirin Challenge Cup]] 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=SAMURAI BLUE (Japan National Team) Squad, Schedule – KIRIN CHALLENGE CUP 2018【9/7＠Hokkaido vs Chile】【9/11＠Osaka vs Costa Rica】|url=http://www.jfa.jp/eng/samuraiblue/news/00018623/|date=30 August 2018|work=jfa.jp|access-date=30 August 2018}}<br />{{cite news|title=19歳で森保ジャパンに抜擢…DF冨安健洋「A代表は違ったものがある」|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?253628-253628-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=3 September 2018|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> It was not until 12 October 2018 when he made his Samurai Blue debut, starting the whole game, in a 3–0 win against [[Panama national football team|Panama]].<ref>{{cite news|title=SAMURAI BLUE、パナマに3–0で2連勝 ～キリンチャレンジカップ2018【10/12＠新潟】～|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/20181012/news/00019109/|publisher=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=12 October 2018|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> Tomiyasu became the first teenager to start in the senior team since [[Ryo Miyaichi]].<ref>{{cite news|title=19歳冨安デビュー、10代ＣＢは初／日本代表先発|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201810120000734.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=ja|date=12 October 2018|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> A month later on 16 November 2018, he made his second appearance for Japan, in a 1–1 draw against [[Venezuela national football team|Venezuela]].<ref>{{cite news|title=森保ジャパン引き分け 初陣からの４連勝ならず|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201811160000907.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=ja|date=16 November 2018|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref>

In December 2018, Tomiyasu was re-called to the Japanese squad for the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=SAMURAI BLUE (Japan National Team) Squad, Schedule – AFC Asian Cup UAE 2019 (1/5-2/1)|url=http://www.jfa.jp/eng/news/00019975/|date=13 December 2018|work=jfa.jp|access-date=1 February 2019}}</ref> He made his tournament debut for the Samurai Blue, starting the whole game and helped Japan win 3–2 against [[Turkmenistan national football team|Turkmenistan]].<ref>{{cite news|title=日本大迫２発、堂安弾でヒヤヒヤ勝利／アジア杯詳細|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201901080001324.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=ja|date=10 January 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> He helped Samurai Blue keep a clean sheet by beating [[Oman national football team|Oman]] 1–0 win to advance to the knockout stage.<ref>{{cite news|title=日本代表、2連勝でアジア杯決勝T進出！ 原口のPK弾でオマーンを下す|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20190114/891839.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=ja|date=14 January 2011|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> He then scored his first goal for Japan, scoring from a header, in a 1–0 win against [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia]] to reach the semi–finals.<ref name="Tomiyasu Saudi Arabia">{{cite news|title=日本８強！冨安Ｖ弾サウジ下す／アジア杯決勝Ｔ詳細|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201901210000391.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=ja|date=21 January 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> Tomiyasu later played two more matches of the tournament, which saw the Samurai Blue reaching the final for the first time since 2011.<ref>{{cite news|title=日本代表、堂安の"VAR弾"でベスト4進出！ FIFAランク100位のベトナムに辛くも勝利|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20190124/897439.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=ja|date=24 January 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title=大迫２発だ！原口１発だ！日本３発決勝 イラン撃破|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201901290000012.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=ja|date=29 January 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> In the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup Final|AFC Asian Cup final]] against Qatar, he started and captained Japan, as the Samurai Blue loss 3–1, finishing as runner–up in the process.<ref name="Tomiyasu Asian Cup">{{cite news|script-title=ja:苦しみ抜いた南野が一矢、小３から変わらぬ強い体幹|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201902020000084.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=ja|date=2 February 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{Cite web |title=Qatar 3–1 Japan (Feb 1, 2019) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/536009 |access-date=1 December 2023 |publisher=ESPN}}</ref>

Following the conclusion to the AFC Asian Cup tournament, Tomiyasu was called up to the [[Japan national football team|Japan squad]] ahead of the [[2019 Copa América|Copa América]] in Brazil.<ref>{{cite news|title=植田が昨年９月以来の招集 再びチャンス来る|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201905240000109.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=ja|date=24 May 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> He started all three matches, playing in the centre–back position, as the Samurai Blue were eliminated in the Group stage.<ref>{{cite news|title=SAMURAI BLUE、初戦は0–4でチリに敗れる～CONMEBOLコパアメリカブラジル2019～|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/news/00021685/|website=Japan Football Association|language=Japanese|date=17 June 2019|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=SAMURAI BLUE、三好選手の2ゴールでウルグアイに引分け～CONMEBOLコパアメリカブラジル2019～|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/copaamerica2019/news/00021729/|website=Japan Football Association|language=Japanese|date=21 June 2019|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title= SAMURAI BLUE エクアドルに引分け、準々決勝進出ならず～CONMEBOLコパアメリカブラジル2019～|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/news/00021776/|website=Japan Football Association|language=Japanese|date=25 June 2019|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> He later played three matches of 2019, helping Japan keep three clean sheets.<ref>{{cite news|title=森保ジャパンが強豪パラグアイを破る／スコア詳細|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201909040000723.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=ja|date=4 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title=日本がミャンマーに快勝！ カタールW杯へ好発進…久保はアジア予選最年少出場記録を更新|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20190910/978162.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=ja|date=10 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title=森保日本６発快勝、モンゴル撃破／Ｗ杯２次予選詳細|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201910100000497.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=ja|date=10 October 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref>

Almost a year absent, Tomiyasu was called up to the Samurai Blue squad on 6 October 2020.<ref>{{cite news|title=南野拓実が代表10番！鎌田９、久保建英17／一覧|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/202010060000931.html|website=Nikkan Sports|language=ja|date=6 October 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> He started three out of the four matches for Japan by the end of the year.<ref>{{cite news|title=久保も南野も不発、森保日本はカメルーンとドロー|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/202010090001198.html|website=Nikkan Sports|language=ja|date=9 October 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=植田直通が劇的ゴール！ 日本、コートジボワールを下して2020年初勝利|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20201014/1130374.html|website=Soccer King|language=ja|date=14 October 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=SAMURAI BLUE メキシコ代表に後半2失点で今季初黒星|url=http://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/news/00025747/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=17 November 2020|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> Tomiyasu made five starts for the Samurai Blue between 7 September 2021 and 16 November 2021, where he formed a partnership with [[Maya Yoshida]].<ref>{{cite news|title=【Match Report】SAMURAI BLUE 大迫選手のゴールで中国代表に勝って最終予選で初勝利|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/worldcup_2022/final_q/20210907/news/00027859/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=7 September 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=【Match Report】SAMURAI BLUE、サウジアラビアに0–1惜敗で勝点積み上げならず|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/worldcup_2022/final_q/news/00028072/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=8 October 2021|access-date=25 May 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=【Match Report】SAMURAI BLUE、オーストラリア代表に2–1勝利で最終予選2勝目|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/worldcup_2022/final_q/20211012/news/00028098/|website=Football Association|language=ja|date=12 October 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=【Match Report】SAMURAI BLUE、伊東選手のゴールでベトナム代表に勝利で3位浮上|url=https://www.jfa.jp/news/00028325/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=12 November 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=【Match Report】SAMURAI BLUE、伊東選手のゴールでオマーンに勝利、最終予選2位浮上|url=https://www.jfa.jp/news/00028357/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=17 November 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> After a year absent, Tomiyasu was called up to the Japan squad on 15 September 2022.<ref>{{cite news|title=9月の欧州遠征に臨む日本代表メンバーが発表！ 冨安、古橋ら30名が招集|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20220915/1689279.html|website=Soccer King|language=ja|date=15 September 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> He was able to make his first appearance for the Samurai Blue in a year, starting the match, in a 2–0 win against [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] on 23 September 2022.<ref>{{cite news|title=日本代表がアメリカ代表に2発快勝！ 先制点の鎌田大地が躍動、三笘薫がトドメの追加点|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20220923/1691894.html|website=Soccer King|language=ja|date=23 September 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> In November 2022, Tomiyasu was called up to the 26-man Japan squad that would compete in [[Qatar]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Japan Squad WC22 |date=5 December 2022 |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/japan-world-cup-2022-squad-hajime-moriyasu-names-his-latest-squad}}<br />{{cite news|title=FIFAワールドカップカタール2022™ SAMURAI BLUE（日本代表）メンバー|url=https://www.jfa.jp/news/00030869/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=1 November 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> He made his World Cup debut, coming on as a second–half substitute, in the Samurai Blue's 2–1 win over [[Germany national football team|Germany]].<ref>{{cite news|title=【Match Report】SAMURAI BLUE、ドイツに歴史的な逆転勝利で白星発進|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/worldcup_2022/news/00031096/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=24 November 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> Tomiyasu came on as a 71st-minute substitute when he helped Japan beat [[Spain national football team|Spain]] win 2–1 to help his country reached the knockout phase.<ref>{{cite news|title=【Ｗ杯】日本、コスタリカ堅守に０－１黒星…１勝１敗で決勝トーナメント進出は一転してピンチに|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/qatar2022/news/202211270001610.html|website=Nikkan Sports|language=ja|date=27 November 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br/>{{cite news|title=【Match Report】SAMURAI BLUE、スペインに逆転勝ちで2大会連続の16強進出|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/worldcup_2022/news/00031164/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=2 December 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> Tomiyasu made his first start in the centre–back position, forming a partnership with Yoshida, against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] in the last-16 of the World Cup, as the match eventually ended 1–1 with the Samurai Blue crashing out after their defeat on penalties.<ref>{{cite news|title=【Match Report】SAMURAI BLUE、クロアチアにPK戦で敗れて16強越えならず|url=http://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/worldcup_2022/news/00031190/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=6 December 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref>

Following the World Cup, Tomiyasu didn't receive a call–up from Japan until on 31 August 2023.<ref>{{cite news|title=SAMURAI BLUE 9月欧州遠征メンバーに冨安選手、田中碧選手らが復帰、初選出に毎熊選手|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue_2023/news/00032717/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=31 August 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> On 9 September 2023, in a friendly match against [[Germany national football team|Germany]], which was his first international match following the World Cup, he displayed solid defence in a 4–1 away victory, in which he was awarded player of the match.<ref>{{Cite tweet |date=12 September 2023 |user=jfa_samuraiblue |number= 1701455287272837209 |title=#冨安健洋 選手に |trans-title=Trophy presented to Tomiyasu}}<br/>{{Cite web|date=9 September 2023 |title=International Friendly Match (against Germany)|url=https://www.jfa.jp/eng/samuraiblue/20230909/match_page.html|access-date=2023-09-11|website=JFA}}<br/>{{cite news|title=「トミーは本物だ」攻守両面で圧巻パフォ！ 日本代表DF冨安健洋がドイツ戦のPOTMに！「別格の活躍でした」|url=https://www.soccerdigestweb.com/news/detail/id=139038|website=Soccer Digest Web|language=ja|date=12 September 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> On 1 January 2024, Tomiyasu was called up to the Japan's squad for the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup|AFC Asian Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite news|title=SAMURAI BLUE（日本代表）メンバー・スケジュール AFCアジアカップカタール2023（2024.1.12～2.10）|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/news/00033539/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=1 January 2024|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> He played four times and helped the Samurai Blues progress all the way to the quarter–finals, where Japan was eliminated by Iran.<ref>{{cite news|title=【Match Report】SAMURAI BLUE、インドネシアに勝利、2位でAFCアジアカップ16強へ進出|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/news/00033613/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=25 January 2024|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=【Match Report】SAMURAI BLUE、バーレーンに3–1勝利でAFCアジアカップ8強進出|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/news/00033627/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=1 February 2024|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{Cite news|title=【Match Report】SAMURAI BLUE、イランに逆転負けでAFCアジアカップ4強ならず|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/news/00033635/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=3 February 2024|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Playing in either at centre back or right back, Tomiyasu is known for being physical, as well as his strong defending structure.<ref>{{cite news|title=Tomiyasu, l'acquisto più inaspettato dell'estate (per ora)|url=https://www.ultimouomo.com/takehiro-tomiyasu-bologna-come-gioca/|publisher=I’Ultimo Uomo|language=it|date=24 August 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title=Calciomercato Bologna, ecco Tomiyasu: chi è il giapponese, nuovo difensore rossoblù|url=https://sport.sky.it/calciomercato/2019/07/09/calciomercato-bologna-tomiyasu-chi-e|publisher=Sky Italia|language=it|date=9 November 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title=Giocatori da prendere a 1 al Fantacalcio|url=https://www.ultimouomo.com/giocatori-da-prendere-a-1-al-fantacalcio/#|publisher=I’Ultimo Uomo|language=it|date=30 August 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite web|url=https://www.bolognafc.it/la-carriera-di-tomiyasu/|title=La carriera di Tomiyasu|publisher=Bologna F.C. 1909|language=it|date=9 July 2019|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190709141301/https://www.bolognafc.it/la-carriera-di-tomiyasu/|archive-date=9 July 2019|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite news|title=Bologna, chiusura senza botti ma c'è il tempo per crescere|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2019/09/03/bologna-chiusura-senza-botti-ma-ce-il-tempo-per-crescereBologna12.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=3 September 2019|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> He's also known for his versatility, capably playing at left back due to his two-footedness.<ref>{{cite news|title=Takehiro Tomiyasu agrees with Arsenal boss Mikel Arteta on his most impressive quality|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/takehiro-tomiyasu-mikel-arteta-arsenal-21578987|website=Football London|date=15 September 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=Every word Mikel Arteta said on Ben White, Zinchenko's fitness and Smith Rowe's injury|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/fixtures-results/arteta-white-zinchenko-smith-rowe-25037783|website=Football London|date=16 September 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=Takehiro Tomiyasu: Arsenal's attack-building defender could prove useful at centre-back|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4855571/2023/09/15/tomiyasu-arsenal-japan-centre-back/|website=The Athletic|date=15 September 2023|access-date=31 October 2023}}</ref>

His performance at [[Sint-Truidense V.V.|Sint-Truiden]] was so impressive that Voetbal Nieuws named him "The Best Eleven of Foreign Players Who Have Left from the [[Belgian First Division A|Jupiler League]]".<ref>{{cite news|title=冨安健洋も選出！ベルギーメディアが選ぶリーグ出身外国籍ベストイレブン|url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2020/04/15/post370732/ |website=Football Channel|language=ja|date=15 April 2020|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> Former teammate [[Pol García]] praised Tomiyasu for his attitude, while former Italy international defender [[Cristian Zaccardo]] praised his strong and energetic performances.<ref>{{cite news|title=冨安健洋にSTVVの元同僚が賛辞「素晴らしい価値ある青年。トップクラブに入れる」|url=https://www.goal.com/jp/%E3%83%8B%E3%83%A5%E3%83%BC%E3%82%B9/%E5%86%A8%E5%AE%89%E5%81%A5%E6%B4%8B%E3%81%ABstvv%E3%81%AE%E5%85%83%E5%90%8C%E5%83%9A%E3%81%8C%E8%B3%9B%E8%BE%9E%E7%B4%A0%E6%99%B4%E3%82%89%E3%81%97%E3%81%84%E4%BE%A1%E5%80%A4%E3%81%82%E3%82%8B%E9%9D%92%E5%B9%B4%E3%83%88%E3%83%83%E3%83%97%E3%82%AF%E3%83%A9%E3%83%96%E3%81%AB%E5%85%A5%E3%82%8C%E3%82%8B/1x2bz93f2gs1v1l5yrku9hwyfn |website=Goal (website)|language=ja|date=20 May 2020|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=元伊代表DFが冨安健洋に賛辞「日本人選手を気に入っている。強くてエネルギッシュ」|url=https://www.goal.com/jp/%E3%83%8B%E3%83%A5%E3%83%BC%E3%82%B9/%E5%85%83%E4%BC%8A%E4%BB%A3%E8%A1%A8df%E3%81%8C%E5%86%A8%E5%AE%89%E5%81%A5%E6%B4%8B%E3%81%AB%E8%B3%9B%E8%BE%9E%E6%97%A5%E6%9C%AC%E4%BA%BA%E9%81%B8%E6%89%8B%E3%82%92%E6%B0%97%E3%81%AB%E5%85%A5%E3%81%A3%E3%81%A6%E3%81%84%E3%82%8B%E5%BC%B7%E3%81%8F%E3%81%A6%E3%82%A8%E3%83%8D%E3%83%AB%E3%82%AE%E3%83%83%E3%82%B7%E3%83%A5/10otkymgb0zjb1ggpjohzn62nb|website=Goal (website)|language=ja|date=22 May 2020|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]]'s technical coach Emilio De Leo said about Tomiyasu's performances, saying: "He has the ability to read and manipulate time and space in a modern way."<ref>{{cite news|title=ボローニャ監督代理、冨安健洋の長所を語る「彼は時間と空間を現代的に操れる」|url=https://www.goal.com/jp/ニュース/ボローニャ監督代理冨安健洋の長所を語る彼は時間と空間を現代的に操れる/1qejs7rw8my5d1huhwe9dh1nyr|website=Goal (website)|language=ja|date=22 May 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> The club manager [[Marco Di Vaio]] agreed, saying: "Tomiyasu immediately impressed us because he is very good with his feet and knows how to adapt to all defense roles."<ref>{{cite news|title=Bologna, Di Vaio a CM: 'Tomiyasu & co, così scopriamo i giovani. Cutrone? Ne parlai col Milan ma...'|url=https://www.calciomercato.com/news/di-vaio-racconta-il-progetto-bologna-a-cm-tomiyasu-e-gli-altri-c-18692|website=Calcio Mercato|language=it|date=27 May 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> National Italian newspaper [[Corriere dello Sport – Stadio|Corriere dello Sport]] praised Tomiyasu's performance, saying: "He is a treasure. The key to reinforcing Bologna".<ref>{{cite news|title=「「トミヤスは黄金だ」"休めないほど不可欠"な冨安健洋をイタリア紙が絶賛！「昨夏の補強で最高の利回り」|url=https://www.soccerdigestweb.com/news/detail/id=76624|website=Soccer Digest Web|language=ja|date=22 July 2020|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref>

Manuel Minguzzi, a reporter for Tuttobologna, said about his performance: "Fans can always expect maximum professionalism and commitment from Tomiyasu. As a full back he did very well, while as a central he made some mistakes, but in Serie A it is quite normal because adaptation is needed. Tomiyasu also possesses great qualities when building the game. I was very struck by the fact that in the first year of Serie A he immediately became the protagonist. He had been taken as a center back but was often used at full back offering both phases of play. As soon as he arrived he became an idol. The Japanese market is always very active on social networks and Bologna has expanded its popularity thanks to Tomiyasu."<ref>{{cite news|title=The view from Italy on what Bologna right-back Takehiro Tomiyasu would have brought Newcastle United|url=https://www.chroniclelive.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/view-italy-what-bologna-right-19083192|website=Chronicle Live|date=10 October 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}<br />{{cite news|title=「セリエA1年目ですぐに主役の座を掴んだことに感銘受けた」伊記者がボローニャで活躍の冨安健洋を称賛|url=https://www.goal.com/jp/ニュース/takehiro-tomiyasu-bologna-202010110330/1ra1kobgdx4ac10zggoh68amxd|website=Goal (website)|language=ja|date=10 October 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> Former Japan manager [[Alberto Zaccheroni]] praised manager [[Siniša Mihajlović]] for using Tomiyasu regularly in the first team, saying: "He was good but not malicious, Mihajlovic did a great job making him play a full back year, in less risky areas, and then use him as a central player after gaining experience."<ref>{{cite news|title=Zaccheroni aspettare stanca lanno buono non arriva mai|url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2021/03/11/zaccheroniaspettare-stanca-lanno-buono-non-arriva-maiBologna11.html|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=11 March 2021|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref>

Reflecting on his first season at Arsenal, Football London said about Tomiyasu: "Defensively immaculate and technically excellent he instantly transformed the right back position from one of weakness into one of strength."<ref>{{cite news|title=Nicolas Pepe awful, Martin Odegaard stars, Bukayo Saka superb – Arsenal season player ratings|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/pepe-saka-odegaard-arsenal-ratings-24036577|website=Football London|date=23 May 2022|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Tomiyasu has two sisters.<ref name="Tomiyasu Interview 1"/> He was planning to follow in his sisters' footsteps by becoming a professional swimmer before switching to football instead, stating that he wanted to be a footballer.<ref name="Tomiyasu Interview 1"/> In his first press conference in Bologna, Tomiyasu said he began to learn Italian and asked the media to call him Tomi.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bologna, Tomiyasu si presenta: "Chiamatemi "Tomi", al di là del ruolo voglio giocare" |url=https://corrieredibologna.corriere.it/bologna/bologna-calcio/19_luglio_23/bologna-tomiyasu-si-presenta-chiamatemi-tomi-di-la-ruolo-voglio-giocare-90a4a81e-ad5c-11e9-9ece-1d74122878de.shtml|publisher=Corriere DI Bologna|language=it|date=23 July 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}<br />{{cite news|title="Marcherò dei campioni, mi piace lottare". Fenucci: "È costato caro e stupirà tutti"|url=https://corrieredibologna.corriere.it/bologna/bologna-calcio/19_luglio_24/marchero-campioni-mi-piace-lottarefenucci-costato-caro-stupira-tutti-b231f67a-adf3-11e9-bb8a-df33d0573529.shtml|publisher=Corriere Di Bologna|language=it|date=24 July 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> By February 2020, Italian media ''Corriere Di Bologna'' reported that Tomiyasu already spoke Italian.<ref>{{cite news|title=Verso Bologna-Genoa senza Soriano, De Leo: "Servirà un approccio determinato"|url=https://corrieredibologna.corriere.it/bologna/bologna-calcio/20_febbraio_14/verso-bologna-genoa-senza-soriano-de-leo-servira-approccio-determinato-44f0e04a-4f2d-11ea-9889-5b43d68a9cd2.shtml|publisher=Corriere Di Bologna|language=it|date=14 February 2020|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> In addition to Italian and his native Japanese, Tomiyasu also speaks English, having sharpened his English skills during his spell in Sint-Truiden.<ref>{{cite news|title=Football: Tomiyasu talking the talk, walking the walk in Europe |url=https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2019/03/504b4f3b2fd8-soccer-tomiyasu-talking-the-talk-walking-the-walk-in-europe.html|agency=Kyodo News|date=28 March 2019|access-date=8 August 2022}}</ref>{{Citation needed|date=September 2023}}

Tomiyasu revealed that growing up, he idolised [[Javier Mascherano]].<ref>{{cite news|title=18歳のJリーガーを支えるバルサスクールでの経験（後編）|url=https://mundodeportivo.jp/articles/1283|work=Mundo Deportivo|language=ja|date=29 April 2017|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> In the wake of the [[COVID-19 pandemic]] in Italy, Tomiyasu spoke out about his life during the pandemic and while the season was suspended, he exercised daily.<ref>{{cite news|title=ボローニャ冨安「接触を避けること」コロナ予防語る|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/world/news/202003280000673.html|website=Nikkan Sports|language=ja|date=28 March 2020|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=冨安健洋、東京五輪延期は「妥当な結果だけど残念」…自宅待機の近況も報告|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/world/ita/20200404/1053120.html|website=Soccer King|language=ja|date=3 April 2020|access-date=12 September 2024}}<br />{{cite news|title=冨安健洋がコロナ禍で心境語る…マスク文化ないイタリア人の意識も「変わった」|url=https://www.goal.com/jp/ニュース/冨安健洋がコロナ禍で心境語るマスク文化ないイタリア人の意識も変わった/ces5vt7xrc2n1u4lmjgfndihh|website=Goal (website)|language=ja|date=20 April 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> On 12 May 2020, his former club, [[Avispa Fukuoka]] expressed their gratitude to Tomiyasu after he donated 1,000 masks to the club's academy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.avispa.co.jp/news/post-30212|title=冨安 健洋 選手よりマスクを寄贈いただきました|website=Avispa Fukuoka|language=ja|date=12 May 2020|access-date=13 August 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200516203010/https://www.avispa.co.jp/news/post-30212|archive-date=16 May 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The following month, Bologna revealed that Tomiyasu were among the players and staff members agreed to give up a month's salary.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bologna fc, c'è l'accordo tra squadra e club: giocatori e staff rinunciano a una mensilità|url=https://corrieredibologna.corriere.it/bologna/bologna-calcio/20_giugno_15/bologna-fc-c-l-accordo-squadra-club-giocatori-staff-rinunciano-una-mensilita-249ab9e8-aecc-11ea-8225-9e5e4b15f1b6.shtml|website=Corriere Di Bologna|language=it|date=15 June 2020|access-date=13 August 2021}}</ref>

On 27 December 2021, he tested positive for [[COVID-19]] amid the [[COVID-19 pandemic in the United Kingdom|pandemic in the United Kingdom]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Tomiyasu, Aubameyang, Maitland-Niles: Arsenal injury news following Norwich City clash|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/tomiyasu-arsenal-injury-news-norwich-22569520|website=Football London|date=27 December 2021|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> Tomiyasu also wears contact lenses on the pitch.<ref>{{cite news|title=Gabriel Jesus, Martin Odegaard – Arsenal injury news and return dates ahead of Brentford clash|url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/gabriel-jesus-martin-odegaard-arsenal-28136760|website=Football London|date=20 November 2023|access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref>

